animal.description:
Bookie the Wookie,

I am a handsome young lad. I didn't have a great start in life. My first owners dumped me down by the river as a young puppy. I lived on scraps thrown to me by the homeless people who lived by the river. I was very scared but some nice people caught me and took me to their home. I saw the vet and got all of my shots and I was neutered (OUCH!) and microchipped. I had a very bad start but I am working on my personal skills. I am very afraid of men and people that I don't know. I love to play, get pets, snacks, and cuddle on the couch. I just want someone who will be my one and only. I'm good with other dogs. I like to chase squirrels, rabbits, and anything that thinks it is too fast for me to catch it. I like to smile when I'm happy to see you and I will wiggle and squirm. I lay down and sleep if I am kept in a crate even if I don't like it. Are you looking for a great hiking buddy? Can you give me the perfect couch to sleep on? If you think you have what it takes to be my perfect furever home, feel free to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
PATRICK: 9 months old, lab shepherd mix, 40 lbs (around 55 lbs full grown), NEEDS home out of the city

He doesn't make the most amazing first impression. On the street, he freaks out all over the place noises and commotion and, like, society in general scare him shitless. At home where he's comfy, he'll hide when you first walk in, he may bark once or twice, then he'll plaster himself to a wall and will only move sideways along it. It doesn't take Patrick long to warm up though. Give him an hour, maybe two, and he'll consider you his new BFF. This 1-year-old shepherd mix is a great big baby, but if you're patient, he's every minute worth it. It's not his fault he came from a hoarding situation in TN a few months ago where he and his litter mates barely had human contact and lived in decrepit filth. He's the shyest of the bunch and the last to find his forever family. Patrick is about 50 lbs, amazing with other dogs and cats, and loves to play fetch and leap through snow. He's a super snuggle muffin and totally gentle. He'll need lots of exercise and an experienced home out of the city with a confident doggy pal and a fenced yard.

His foster mom says: Patrick is a playful, fun-loving pup that would do very well in an active home that has some space for him to run around and expel all his puppy energy. He loves his toys and doing zoomies in the yard.Cuddle bug doesn't begin to describe this baby boy, so when not playing with his foster siblings, he is cuddling with his foster humans and pretty much wants to be on top of them wherever they are stationary.Patrick is still skittish and will hide around any people he doesn't know that are entering his space, but will warm up to anyone his humans welcome into the home consistently. He is a gentle and sweet pup with no signs of aggression to children or other dogs/animals of any size or breed. He doesn't seem to have any interest in being the alpha male in a pack; just very happy to be included and loved.Patrick is house trained and is doing very well with name recognition and recall as well as his leash work. With continued love, patience and guidance, Patrick will be the perfect addition to any family.Patrick will do best in an active home with parents who will continue his training. He is incredibly bright and a very sensitive guy who's only desire is to love and be loved.

PLEASE NOTE: This animal is not at the Social Tees office all of our dogs and cats are in foster homes while they wait to find their forever families. :) If youd like to apply to adopt this pet, please complete an adoption application at socialteesnyc.org. Because we are a small team and receive hundreds of applications each week, we are unable to respond to every application and every inquiry email, but we do our best. Please have patience! If your application is approved, you will for sure hear from us. If you have questions, please take a look at the Adoption and Fostering FAQs etc. on our website as all common questions are answered there. Thank you for your understanding and flexibility as we work to save these innocent lives!! 

LEARN MORE ABOUT US: socialteesnyc.org; Instagram via @socialteesnyc; Facebook.com/socialteesanimalrescue

animal.description:
The Milo Foundation AnimalID is 28163 and the Current Location is at the Milo Sanctuary. 

One of a pair of hybrid type fellows who arrived via a small rescue in the Sacramento area. These are truly delightful creatures who just love romping and playing in the wooded hills at our Sanctuary! They have two delightful girlfriends in their pack and the foursome immediately took to each other like long lost friends (or family members!) Blue-eyed Sinatra is not a dog who chooses human company, though he is sweet, sensitive, curious and does engage, but chooses dogs over humans. We respect that choice and give him and the others the time and a big space to call home - eventually in the right circumstances with the right kinds of people and other dog(s) we can consider placing them, or they'll stay here and have their friends and good food and a happy life!

Thank you for considering adoption of a Milo Foundation Sanctuary dog.
Our Sanctuary is where our rescued dogs who have had difficulty in a home in the past, have behavioural issues, or too much energy, or for some, aggression issues with other dogs, or intense stranger danger that make them more difficult to safely and happily live in urban environments.
These are not beginner dogs or for the most part nor are they for families with children. IF you are looking for an easy dog to add to your family, we suggest looking at the dogs at our Adoption Center, Milo Pt Richmond. 
BUT, if you can offer a safe and nurturing home to a dog with some behavioural "quirks" please do send an application today. Thank you.

animal.description:
Roach is finally accepting applications!

Many know this boy's history but if you do not here is the short version. Roach's previous owner had to move in with a friend and was unable to bring Roach so he went to stay with a friend for a while. Unfortunately the friend's neighbor was not keen on Roach or likely any dogs. Somehow he ended up throwing a machete at him and severing a large portion of his back. It went down to the spine but thankfully did not damage any major spinal nerves or the cord. He was thankfully surrendered to our friends at Turtle Mountain Animal Rescue.
We had just finished Petey's (our tilapia fish graft dog) recovery and when we heard about Roach we reached out to offer any help they needed. Roach was ultimately transferred to our care due to the lengthly drive to the nearest vet to TMAR and the many visits he would have needed. We were happy to help. We started him on medications and special topical concoctions for his bandage on his back along with cold laser therapy. He healed extremely fast.
We did notice that he continued to be both urine and fecal incontinent and we wondered if the machete had actually done damage to his spinal cord so we took him in for an MRI. That revealed that thankfully the machete wound did not damage anything internal. However, it also showed that he had a healed fractured vertebra in his pelvis. This was not related to the machete incident and we later found out that his tail/rear end was run over by a car 9 months prior to the machete incident. The vertebra healed but was still causing nerve damage. It was part of what helps wag his tail. Every time Roach would wag his tail he was potentially causing more nerve damage. If we wanted to preserve what function he had left of his bladder and bowels we needed to remove his tail as far up as possible.
We have also placed him on a urinary incontinent medication called Proin that he takes once daily (about $25per month). He will likely need this for life. He can go out and empty his bladder but he will continue to drip little drops. For this reason we have some belly bands that he will wear inside the home. They do not bother him a bit. As for the fecal incontinence, this is a little more complex. There is not medication to help this but it is not out of control. He doesn't purposefully defecate like he urinates so it will just fall out. He has wonderfully formed stool so it is not diarrhea at all.
He will need to remain on a specific brand of food called Hills Biome (prescription $63/bag which lasts about 4-6 weeks) that will keep him regular as his gut is not able to move things through like a normal dog. This food has probiotics and prebiotics to help keep his gut happy.

We know that it will be difficult to find a home that will accept an incontinent dog. His personality makes up for it ten fold. This boy has been through so much! We think that a home that loves spending a lot of time out side would be best. He would love to be a farm dog and keep things in line, however we require that they live inside. He gets along with most dogs but does not appreciate intact males nor does he like in your face dogs. He doesn't seem to mind cats.

If you think you have the right home for Roach please send in an application at RPAW.org
Adoption fee is $300

animal.description:
PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE AT WWW.PITRESCUE.ORG FOR INFORMATION ON OUR ORGANIZATION, ADOPTION POLICIES AND PROCESS, EDUCATIONAL INFORMATION, AND A FULL LIST OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS ALONG WITH PHOTOS AND FULL BIOS!!!
More pictures and info on this particular dog visit: https://www.pitrescue.org/arthurfonzarelli

Apply online: http://fs22.formsite.com/siouxempire/form1/index.html?1316620486706

*Adoption application must be filled out with home visit and references (personal and vet) required prior to any adoption. Filling out an application does not obligate you to adopt, but merely begins the process. SEPR DOES adopt out of state!

Adoption fees:All SEPR adoptions are $300.  This includes: adoption fee (spay/neuter, utd vaccinations, micro-chipping), microchip registration, Gentle Leader, and two tie downs for use in your home. 

SEPR requires all adopted dogs attend a training class with their adoptive family within 90 days of their adoption. If an adoptive family completes this training class, they will be refunded $100 of their adoption fee with proof of licensed certificate. SEPR even offers an obedience class called Train-A-Bull to alumni over 1 year of age on a seasonal basis.  These classes are currently free!

*All other pets in the residence must be spayed or neutered and all pets up to date on vaccinations.

*SEPR requires all applicants must be 21 years of age.

*SEPR dogs are adopted to be inside the home, “part of the family” dogs only.

*Families with children 4 years of age and under wanting to adopt puppies will be reviewed on a case by case basis. Raising a puppy properly takes a lot of time, and we understand that in families with small children, time can be a limited commodity.

animal.description:
Hello, I'm Keaton and I am a 3 year old boxer mix! I am about 72 lbs.

I would feel most comfortable in a home with low to no commotion. I was adopted out as a puppy and kept outside with little to no socialization for my entire life. Adults only please! I am looking for a family to show me what love is and let me be the indoor family member Pawmetto Lifeline knows I can be. My adoption is considered "Best Match". This means that I am looking for a specific type of home or certain qualities in my new family. I am not first come-first serve for any approved applicant. Pawmetto Lifeline's adoption advocates and my case managers would love to review your application to see if we are a good fit. 

My adoption fee of $200 includes my up-to-date vaccinations, microchip, deworming, and I come home spayed/neutered. I even started on my monthly flea and heartworm preventatives - what more could you ask for?

If you'd like to meet me, please fill out an application on our website, PawmettoLifeline.org, and an adoption advocate will be with you shortly. Thank you!

Maya was at a shelter a few miles north of New Orleans, Louisiana. Cane Haven Rescue pulled her from the shelter to give her another chance at life. Maya is approximately 5 years old, up to date on vaccinations, spayed & microchipped.

Maya is house trained, kennel trained & knows her basic commands/manners. 

Interested adopters can fill out an application at canehavenrescue.com. 
Any possible questions about Maya, please email canehavenrescue@gmail.com 

Cane Haven Rescue will transport any of their adoptable dogs to the right home. We do require adoption fees that are based on the age & health status of the adoptable dog. The adoption fee covers every single dog in CHR with vaccinations, heartworm test, deworming, microchip, spay/neuter & medications. All CHR adoptable dogs are current on their monthly  heartworm and flea medication. A CHR representative will do a home check to ensure the pets are placed in a secure and loving home.

animal.description: Ruger IS AVAILALBE (updated 02-02-2021).To meet any of our dogs you must first complete our online adoption application on our website. For more information and the adoption application for Ruger, please visit our website belowhttp://www.coastalgsr.org/dog_profile.php?ID=22258&name=RugerAs a puppy, Ruger turned up at the shelter after seemingly having been hit by a car. We rescued him and immediately sent him to our vet, where we discovered that he'd sustained four fractures, including one to his pelvis. He had multiple surgeries and then left the hospital to recover in a foster home.Since his rescue, he's more than doubled in size! Just over a year old, he now enjoys running and playing with his foster siblings and having a grand old time, even though he still has a little 'kink' in one back leg. Ruger is crate trained, potty trained, and good with other dogs, but he can be overly rambunctious for little dogs. We are unsure of Ruger's mix... maybe GSD and Basenji? Whatever it is, he's a medium sized boy who is very sweet, has tons of puppy energy, and likes to have a toy in his mouth at all times. If you're looking for an active boy who walks a little funny, but isn't in any pain and is looking for a fun household to call his own, this curly tailed boy is your dream come true! The minimum adoption donation for adults is $375 and the adoption donation for puppies is $500. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is tax deductible. The adoption donation provides that all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis ( i.e., puppies who will need to be altered by 6 mos old). Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

animal.description:
COURTESY POST...NEW ALBANY, OH

Meet Waylon

This adorable boy is a 5 year old Bluetick Coonhound who loves going on walks and snoozing on the sofa. He likes a mix of active and chill time, and would never say no to someone who wants to pet him! Like any introvert, lots of new people and places are tiring, so Waylon would do best in a quieter home where he is the only pet. Young, active children won't be a good fit. No cats please.

Waylon is a classic example of a hound with a strong nose for smelling. Because of this, he needs a fenced-in backyard and someone to continue working with him on his leash manners. He'd love to have a job if you're up for teaching him new tricks. Currently, Waylon is a bit overweight and is working hard to shed some of those extra pounds.

Waylon's adoption fee is $300 US funds. If he sounds like a fit for your home and you'd like to meet him, apply today at rescuedohio.org!

Please note this is a courtesy post and Gentle Jake's is not accepting applications for Waylon directly. Please visit www.rescuedohio.org for more information.

Please Note:

We are all volunteers and busy taking care of our foster dogs so please take the time to fill out our on-line adoption application if you are interested in more information about any of the hounds that we have for adoption. Filling out our application does not obligate you to adopt in any way. It does, however, help us to determine if the dog that your interested in would be a good match for your family and lifestyle.

All of our dogs are fully vetted. They have been vaccinated, altered, microchipped and heartworm tested and on prevention.

VISIT COONHOUND COMPANIONS WEBSITE TO SEE WHY ADOPTING A COONHOUND CAN BE A WONDERFUL EXPERIENCE!

www.coonhoundcompanions.com

ADOPTION FEE: $300.00 US funds

LOCATION: Waylon is currently in foster care in New Albany, OH. With the help of volunteers, transportation to his forever home can possibly be arranged. Don't let distance deter you!

If you would like to give this handsome boy a forever home please fill out our on line adoption application at

www.rescuedohio.org

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet fifty-five pound, 10-year-old Milk. She is one of sixty dogs from a Santa Rosa County hoarding case. For the last few months, she has been experiencing a more respectable pet life in her foster mom's home. Now, after the building up of her health and trust level, it is about time that Sweet Milk gets to be that one-in-a-million companion dog she was always meant to be. She's got the typical Lab temperament - desiring to please and be obedient - and she truly wants nothing more than to be with her person. Her ideal family would be one who is mostly home, who's also gentle in nature themselves, and who deeply enjoys a close relationship with their pets. Other mature pets in the home and going on outings are good options for Milk, but they are also not necessary. Because Milky Mae May's understanding of a safe world is still evolving, busy households or ones with young children may be a bit too much stimulation for her at this stage of her learning. If you feel a possible connection with this sweet soul and have a tender, loving home to offer her, then please contact us for more information. With having lived for so long with so much neglect in the past, we are committed to pairing Milk with a family who can make the rest of her life her absolute best life. Might that be you?

Amazing Grace Bully Rescue is a foster based rescue in the Pensacola, Florida area. We do not have a physical building. If you would like to meet any of our pups, the first step is to fill out our online application so we can contact you.

Our adoption fee for is $150/$175 and includes four sets of puppy shots, two dewormings (done prior to adoption) his/her spay/neuter, current shots, rabies vaccine, and a registered microchip.

If you would like to adopt this Amazing dog, please fill out our online adoption application at www.amazinggracebullyrescue.org

If you have any questions, please text your question to 723-2037. You may also send a message to our Amazing Grace Bully Rescue Page on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, or send an email directly to amazinggracebullyrescue@gmail.com

Disclaimer: We are located in the Pensacola, Florida area and will consider local applicants first, especially with puppies since we use a vet in the local area.

animal.description:
*** Available to Foster & Adopt ***

Suitable for a first time owner
Age: 7 years
Weight: 46lbs
From: Mexico
Serve Neglect Case
James Dean has spent his whole life a prisoner to breeding, with his friend Marilyn who is also available for adoption
Him and Marilyn were used for breeding in the US and once the owner had no use for him any more he dumped them both in Mexico. He came to us covered in ticks and is still severely underweight, but is now a heathy boy. 

James is a wonderful and amazingly sweet dog even after all he’s been through. He holds no grudge against people even though he was spent most of his life severely neglectd and abused, he still loves all people. James is a very easy going boy who would make a great family dog but wouldn’t mind living in a home with just one or two people either. He loves affection and enjoys to spend time just hanging out with his humans. He really loves going out for walks and going out for adventures! (Does great on car rides). Despite his older age he can still handle pretty long walks and easy hiking trails without a problem as long as they are nothing to intense. He is frequently taken out for 1 hour walks and easily hiking trials by our volunteers. James would need to be a only dog, he doesn’t seem to enjoy the Company of other dogs or do particularly well with other dogs. He is a people dog. He could use a little bit of leash training but doesn’t need anything major (pulls a little bit). He also loves very much loves toys. We have seen a few minor instances of him being a little possessive over his food/toys. This is probably due to the fact that he was starved and came to us as a complete skeleton. We don’t think we would be great with younger kids that might yank on him or not no how to respect his personal space, but would be fine in a home with older kids (preteens and up). Over all James is such a wonderful easy going and loving boy who just needs someone who love him through the rest of his days. He is a fan favorite by most of our volunteers and staff.



Apply to foster at:
https://www.animalhopeandwellness.org/fosterprocessandapplication

Apply to adopt at: https://www.animalhopeandwellness.org/adoptionandfosterapplication

We are by appointment only. You must submit and have an approved application before meeting AHWF animals.

For General Adopt/Foster Inquiries: adopt@animalhopeandwellness.org

animal.description:
We will start with Rojo is not animal friendly. He doesn't like other dogs, he doesn't like cats, so far we haven't found any animal that he likes. Rojo is young. He's about one and a half years old. He had a family once. Then he started trying to get the dog on the other side of the fence, so his family decided to rehome him. Well as usual with rehoming to just anyone, Rojo was found wandering the streets a few months later. Rojo has been at animal control for about 6 months. No one ever came for him. Rojo will take a very special adopter. One that doesn't have animals around their yard. One that has a very sturdy privacy fence and one that we don't have to worry about him escaping from the house. Rojo is good with people. He is very high anxiety in animal control. This is understandable because he gets very little socialization other than a walk once or twice a week and a few car rides. I do try to take him to the dog park a couple times a week just to give him a little time away from the shelter to decompress. Rojo is about 70 lbs. We do not recommend children at this time because of his anxiety and he would need time to decompress. He does get overly excited at times. Rojo has been evaluated by a trainer and will be beginning a training program in the near future. If you think you could be the right person for Rojo, please complete an application located here. If Rojo is adopted before his training sessions, they will be included in his adoption.

https://form.jotform.com/31997643682166

animal.description:
Jesse is strikingly handsome 7-9 month old, 35 lb. Lab mix. He is very connected to his people and likes to be with them, even if it's quietly laying at their feet. This sweet boy is just beginning to learn the real joys of a loving home, and he's loving it! Jesse is good with other dogs. Jesse would really like a canine buddy.  He can be a little timid in new situations and takes a little while to bond with his people, so he would prefer a home without young children.

Jesse walks well on leash, is housetrained, sleeps through the night, and is working on his basic commands. He is highly food motivated and very eager to please, making him a quick learner. You know you want some of Jesse's delightful tail wags in your life!


Thank you so much for your interest in adopting a dog from A New Chance Animal Rescue (https://anewchancear.org). We are a 501c3, tax deductible organization. ANCAR is a foster-based rescue, and we adopt within a 90 mile radius of Bedford Hills, NY.  You will find the adoption application here: (https://anewchancear.org/adopt/adoption-application/).  All fields on the application must be completed.
Please read about the adoption process (https://anewchancear.org/adopt/adoption-process/) so you'll know what to expect when you submit.   

Our dogs are in foster care and we do NOT have a shelter or boarding facility. AN APPLICATION MUST BE COMPLETED IN FULL AND APPROVED BEFORE A DOG CAN BE MET. This is a firm policy. Our busy volunteers are not able to respond to questions about the dog or dog meeting requests in the absence of an application.  We know these dogs very well because they are in foster care. Please read the profiles of the dog(s) you are interested in prior to submitting an application.  If there are specific requirements stated (ie: Fenced Yard or Canine Friend Required) these are included because they are vital to the happiness, health, safety and adoption success of that dog. 

We are only able to save as many dogs as we have foster homes (https://anewchancear.org/foster/faqs/) and resources for. We provide medical care including vaccinations, testing, deworming, spaying/neutering and microchipping before transporting our dogs. We provide all supplies, preventatives and any follow up vet care necessary while they are in foster care. These costs are high and the number of lives we can save is entirely dependent upon donations from people like you.  We do not receive funding from private foundations or government sources. If you can find room in your heart to help us, with any amount, we are truly grateful (https://anewchancear.org/help/donate/). We are a 501c3 organization, so all donations are tax-deductible. It is only through the kindness of supporters like you that we are 'changing lives...one tail at a time' by providing our dogs with 'A New Chance.' (https://anewchancear.org) 

Thanks so much.

animal.description:
Carolina Boxer Rescue is a volunteer run, 501(c)3 non-profit organization. Our mission: To balance the health, safety, and welfare needs of Boxers in the Carolinas (and parts of Virginia and Georgia) by providing a loving and safe environment for stray, abused, impounded and owner surrendered dogs by placing them in foster homes and ultimately - forever homes.

________________________________________________________________________________________

Dog's Name: Jackie

Dog's Approximate Age: 4 years

Gender: Female

Dog's Size: Medium (50lbs to 70lbs. as adult and healthy weight)

Dog's Weight: 50 pounds

Good with small dogs?: Yes

Good with big dogs?: Yes

Good with cats?: Yes

Good with kids?: No

Any medical issues?: Anxiety

Crate trained?: Working on it

House trained?: Working on it

Heartworms?: Yes

9/26/20: My favorite things are dogs!! I love all dogs. In fact I will need to live in a home with at least one other confident dog to live my best life. I look to my fur sibling for examples of how to interpret and respond to the world around me. With my sibling I am playful, gentle and clown like at times.

My least favorite things are loud noises and sudden unpredictable movements. For this reason I would really rather be your only "child". I would thrive with a single adult or couple who are quiet and predictable. Yelling and crowds are not enjoyable for me. Can we cuddle on the couch and watch TV together?
I am quiet and gentle. I do not jump on people or loose my mind when someone knocks on the door; that's for amateurs.
I am walking very well on the leash when not startled. I no longer pull or zig zag like a drunken sailor; foster mom said I was better than that and I agree. I don't even react to squirrels. Even though I love dogs, I do not break my stride when we encounter one; I know you depend on me to keep you on task.
Oh yeah.. I am not a door darter either. I sit patiently and wait to be called out the door. I know...I am all you ever wanted in a smooshie faced wiggle bum. Keep your eyes peeled for more updates. I will be ready to come home soon! Thank you for stopping by~ Jackie

_____________________________________________________________________________________

9/16/20: Jackie has come a long way, she has settled in to life with us but really needs a forever home and would love to have another dog around. We heard her bark for the first time the other day while playing in the back yard, we were beginning to wonder if she could. She loves playing chase with our 5yo daughter and has started playing tug of war as well. She has finished her doxy for hearworm but got use to getting a little cheese twice a day and seems to like that routine. She loves being outside and really likes the short walks we have started. She is starting to learn how to walk on a leash but is still easily distracted.

____________________________________________________________________________

8/17/20: Jackie is the sweetest girl. We think she was mostly kept outside where she prefers to be most of the time, unless the sky rumbles then she is ready to come in. She appears to be house trained as we have not had a single accident since we've had her. She is very shy and quiet, we still dont know what her bark sounds like. She is Heartworm Positive and is being treated. Jackie is very independant but is warming up to us every day. When she arrived she was very thin and we looking forward to seeing her at a healthy weight.

_____________________________________________________________________________

Come visit carolinaboxerrescue.org to learn more about me and see more pictures. Learn about our adoption process too!

_____________________________________________________________________________

animal.description:
Meet Ziggy! Sweet Zigglet came in to rescue from living in a car after having to leave her home due to a messy divorce. She is a gorgeous blue brindle American Pitbull Terrier, about 3 years old and spayed. She’s up to date on vaccines and heartworm negative. Ziggy loves humans- every adult and child she meets is her best friend!  She really just wants to cuddle and spend time with someone, affection is all she needs to be happy. She is very well trained; she knows sit, stay, down and is working on her leash manners. She is kennel and house trained, as well. She is kenneled when left alone, but would probably be fine out and about. The kennel is a precaution as there are other dogs in her foster home currently. She's easily entertained with ANY toy, she'll take whatever you give her, as long as she can chew it and carry it around- if it has a squeaker, you just made her day! She also likes to chase her balls, but she's working on bringing them back ha! She's got the sweetest, most telling eyes and they are a true reflection of her good nature. 



Ziggy does need to be the only animal in the home. She was not socialized at all and came from a very hectic, stressful household. She can be unpredictable with dogs and will require an owner that can adhere to those needs. She just needs someone that will be responsible and stick to her training, Ziggy thrives on a routine and discipline. Even so, this girl is absolutely worth it. She will bring so much light in your life and has just been a joy to foster. She is the complete package, she's got to have one little flaw right?! If you're searching for a precious little pittie, with a slight under bite and a huge heart, Ziggy the Piggy is your girl!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our dogs are healthy, spayed/neutered, vaccinated and on heartworm preventative. They live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. Many have basic obedience skills and all have been temperament tested. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, please visit our website to complete an application: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt
(please note: app cannot be done on a mobile device)

For additional information see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Mellow. Pittie. Male. 70lbs. Dogs.

Hi! It’s me, Mellow. I haven’t had one single person interested in adopting me. Gratefully speaking my middle name is resilience so I’m not beating myself up about it. But, I did figure we can use this platform or a moment to talk about who I am. For starters, I am awesome. Ha. I am though. I survived a fairly dark time of 6 whole months in a shelter with the help of my friends at @next.stop.home.chicago. I made into this Pack of Rebels because I was one of the last left behind when our friends were asked to not return to help dogs at the shelter. MCP didn’t have a foster so I went straight into a board and train at @seespotrunchicago and gained more incredible humans into my life. I crushed leash skill and commands. I yearn to learn, baby! That’s me. For real. I was so board for so long, given the opportunity to learn is heaven on Earth as far as I’m concerned. I’m now being fostered at @lovepacklife and have EVEN MORE FRIENDS! I have so many dog friends and so many human friends. I’m extremely grateful. One thing I don’t have is someone who sees me as a Forever plus one. I will make an AMAZING adventure dog! Best friend? Whaaaat?! I was born to be the bestest friend. I have what they call a LUST FOR LIFE. Do you? I’m that ride or die type of love. I cannot wait to share all my treasures with that human willing to call me Home. I promise I will not disappoint. Till then, my friends, stay safe and keep your hearts open. - Mellow

PS. I EVEN beat heartworm!!

animal.description:
Location: New Orleans, Louisiana 

Stella was a owner surrender to a shelter in North Louisiana. Cane Haven Rescue pulled her from the shelter to give her another chance at life. Stella is approximately 3 years old, up to date on vaccinations, spayed & microchipped. 

Stella was at the shelter since December 2019 when her owners decided they no longer wanted her anymore. When her owners found out that a rescue stepped in, they became very irate. We are unsure why they would want Stella locked behind bars, especially since they did not want her. Since December, the shelter staff was weary of Stella because she was extremely scared and the shelter life started to wear on her. She had ZERO human interaction for months. Stella had an angel on her side.. a volunteer took to Stella and started working with her. Stella does take a bit to warm up to new people and her surrounding, but we do not blame her. A meet and greet with any other dogs in the home is mandatory. Stella is also going through a training program to help socialize her back into life. Any new owner must be willing to participate in these sessions. 

Stella is house trained, kennel trained & knows her basic commands/manners. She is an extremely strong girl who sometimes does not realize how strong she actually is. When walking, Stella needs someone who can control her on a leash.

Interested adopters can fill out an application at canehavenrescue.com. 
Any possible questions about Stella, please email canehavenrescue@gmail.com 

Cane Haven Rescue will transport any of their adoptable dogs to the right home. We do require adoption fees that are based on the age & health status of the adoptable dog. The adoption fee covers every single dog in CHR with vaccinations, heartworm test, deworming, microchip, spay/neuter & medications. All CHR adoptable dogs are current on their monthly  heartworm and flea medication. A CHR representative will do a home check to ensure the pets are placed in a secure and loving home. 

www.canehavenrescue.com

animal.description:
"If you're lucky, a dog will come into your life, steal your heart, and change everything!" Meet Oscar, a 3-year-old good-natured Great Pyrenees. This stunning, tall, predominately white Pyr stands out in a crowd with his regal appearance.

He greets people with his charming and kind disposition. This easy-going Pyr would thrive with an active family with older kids, an energetic resident canine who enjoys walks, hiking, and adventures. He requires a home with a fenced yard to play, run, and exercise. He will do best in a family with no cats and no little children. Oscar is cautious when meeting other dogs.

Oscar is housetrained and has had some basic training. He needs a confident leader who can provide firm but loving boundaries because Pyrs are exceptionally smart and need to be challenged.

Oscar has all the traits and qualities to become a loving, devoted family companion. Will Oscar be the one to steal your heart and change your life? If you think he would, please complete an application today.

All dogs and puppies require VISIBLE fencing

Adoption Fee: $300 (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Adoption applications can be found on our website at https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org. Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($225).

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

animal.description:
Meet Casanova! This two year old lovable introvert is ready and waiting for his adopters!

True to his name this sweet boy is a lover. Casanova is an incredibly sweet dog once he knows you. He enjoys cuddling on the couch, playing in the backyard, and hanging out with his foster mom and the other foster dog in his foster home.
Casanova is timid of new people but given a little time to meet you, he'll become one of the best friends you have! Once he's your friend, you have a friend for life! And once he loves you, he doesn't want to see you go. He does best in a travel crate when you're gone from the house, but has shown some ability to be left out while his foster family is gone from the home.

Are you more of the type that likes to watch the latest releases on Netflix than going on a big grand adventure? Casanova would LOVE to join you! Casanova thrives when he knows his environment & structure, and can stay at home in his comfort zone.

This adorable boy is potty trained, neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, and heartworm negative. His adoption fee is $200.

Interested in becoming Casanova's forever family? Shoot us an application to start the adoption process!! http://mhrindy.org/adoption-inquiry/***Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.***

animal.description:
Hey there! I'm Freckles and my life has changed A LOT the past few months. See, my foster momma says she "integrated" me into her "ZooCrew" which are her special doggies and I'm pretty special so that's where I needed to be. Before that I was always outside, with my brothers who have been adopted or are in a foster away from me. I like it and get to meet new doggies often and I have 2 buddies named Lucky and Hemi that I just LOVE!!! I lick their faces, am all wiggly when I get out of the crate to go outside for a while. Hemi don't like it much and sometimes he chases me away and then we wrestle and run around. I get into trouble with Lucky cuz him and I are bigger and we get running, jumping and tearing through the house we have so much fun we forget that we're inside. Sunday I laughed so hard when Lucky fell off the bed but then I forgot and I fell off the bed which wasn't as funny but he thought so. I like it here a lot but I think it's time to free up a spot for a dog in need and that means I need adopted.
Now foster momma says I'm whatever a "diamond in the rough" and with some training I will be the bestest dog ever. I do know how to sit, I can be lured into a crate with special treats and will go to sleep but I would rather sleep on the bed with you. I do have a bad habit or two of pulling things from the garbage or sampling shoes or dirty laundry on occasion but it smells like you so how can you blame me, right?
I need time to get to know you when we first meet and I'll need some practice going places, being on leash, riding in the car, your friends need to give me time to get used to them and I will because foster momma says I'm a "rock star" and that I can do anything!!!

Freckles is a 1 year old heeler/border collie mix. He is current on vaccinations, neutered, microchipped and ready to love you. He is a little shy at first, but once you earn his trust, he will be your best friend!

animal.description:
Howdy! My name is Skylar, and I'm a 9 month old affectionate and playful Lab mix. I just love being around people and love to play! I do great with dogs and kids too. I enjoy going on walks and getting lots of sniffs in and seeing new things. I listen so intently with my ears, they sometimes come together completely! I'm just so stink'n cute! I like to play with toys, especially the stuffed squeaker toys that make funny noises when I chew them. I'm even good about only chewing on my toys instead of other things around the house. I enjoy hanging out outside and love to run. I also like to snuggle inside with my family especially when I've run all out of my puppy energy. I love getting petted and giving kisses in return! I am super smart, and have already learned how to sit, lay down, shake, and stay. I also am crate trained and sleep in my crate all night.

If I sound like the right fit for your family, be sure to send in an application at www.soca-fbc.org/adoptables. My adoption fee is $350 locally or $550 for Bellevue, WA (includes health cert and travel fee). I am up to date on all my shots, spayed and microchipped. I can't wait to meet my new family, and hope to give all my love to them soon!

animal.description:
Meet this adorable Sweetie Pie. She is Sammie Sweetie Pie our senior beauty. Sammie Sweetie Pie has been incredibly lucky. She was hit by two cars in 24 hours. She didn't have any internal injuries!! A true miracle for her

Sammie Sweeite Pie will take a little bit to get to know you. She will love you if you hold some sweet potato chips in your hand. Once she feels safe then you can see how truly amazing she is. She loves to play with other dogs once sure they are ok to be trusted. She does a lot better with Small Male Dogs. 

Sammie Sweetie Pie does well in a household with a backyard. She really enjoys her time in the sun. She is housebroken and leash trained. We are working with her on crate training. She doesn't want to miss out on anything thats going on in the house. 

Sammie Sweetie Pie's foster says she is kind and calm. She takes a moment to open up, but loves the dogs that are her friends.

Covid 19 has changed everything including animal adoptions. We are no longer having meet & greets to keep us safe. We are not conducting home checks for the same reason. We had to keep all our available dogs with our Houston Fosters until adoption. We do everything via video chat, phone conversations, photo sharing, and whatever else we have to do to make this a successful adoption. We are excited to say our adoptions are more today than before the pandemic.

We have a transport service that leaves Houston every 2 weeks. We only use 1 transport service. The owner drives the truck and takes excellent care of our animals. We love those happy relaxed rescue babie's pictures when they arrive and meet their owners! They arrive calmed. The additional fee if adopting outside of the Houston area is $200.

Our adoption fees for Cats & Dogs are: Up to 1 year Old $400 / 13 months and Up $300 

Our adoption application is located at www.springbranchrescue.org Please send any adoption questions to us springbranchrescue@gmail.com

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hi everyone! My name is Maddie, I've been spending time with my friends healing and I am eager to meet my forever family. Something you might not know about me is that I am called Maddie the Magnificent! I got that nickname by overcoming different medical issues after being brought to the London Sanctuary. They took me in and treated me for demodex (its not contagious!) and a few other things. I'm well on my way to recovery and I'm looking for a family to love on and give me all the belly rubs! While I walk great on a leash, I can be curious to see other dogs we encounter on walks. I'll bark to let foster mom know I want to say hi! Everyone is super surprised that I don't bey like a "normal" hound. Don't they know we are all unique?! I am also a master at commands like Sit, Come and Paw. Next to belly rubs, playing with my stuffies is another favorite past time. But then again, so are long walks with my foster family! I love my foster siblings, but I think I'd enjoy a quiet family that loves relaxation as much as me! I'd love to meet you and show you how magnificent I am in person.

About Me:

Loves humans and attention from them
Gets along with other dogs but would prefer to just be single and mingle but plays when she wants to
Has a calm nature
Loves belly rubs
Not a fan of thunderstorms
House trained
Leash trained
Knows sit and paw
Not cat tested
Check out my transformation from Caterpillar to Butterfly at Maddie the Magnificent - From Caterpillar to Butterfly on Facebook.

Maddie is spayed and micro-chipped and up to date on her vaccinations and deworming. She is fostered in Jacksonville; to set up a meet and sniff just send a msg to The London Sanctuary. Her adoption fee is only $250, which includes the above-mentioned vetting. Home visit and reference checks are required and are NOT negotiable. Note that we cannot adopt to those in apartments or other attached housing. Our apologies for the inconvenience.

Gertie Girl is not available for adoption as she has lots of healing and vetting to do yet, but stay tuned for more info!!Not available for adoption until all vetting is completed and after our foster home learns more about this great Doberman, we are, however, accepting applications. Stay tuned for more information!

Gertie Girl came into DRM through our rescue partners in the South. She was brought into the shelter unable to walk and severely emaciated. Her not being able to walk was most likely due to not getting the proper nutrition or food and being combined in a kennel too small for her. The good news is that she doesn't have any muscular or skeletal issues and with structured and continuous physical therapy she will regain the use of her legs. She is such a sweet girl and is just a love bug. Stay tuned as her foster family helps her get healthy!

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

animal.description: Hi I’m Luca!  My name means light, or bringer of light.  That’s EXACTLY what you’ll get if you take me home with you!  I’m a pretty special boy.  I was running on a highway in Nevada for a long time and quite scared.  A very kind soul stopped and spent 3 hours sitting with me until I trusted him enough to let him touch me and take me for a ride.  We got to another place that was kind of loud and scary, but the wonderful people at Moonsong sprung me!  It takes me a few minutes to learn about new people and know that they aren’t scary, and I really like the other dogs that I’ve met!  Since I’ve been at my foster home, I’ve been pretty happy and content, the only thing that I DON’T like so far is when I can SEE my foster mom but I just CAN’T get to her!  Then I bark, bark, bark till she comes over.  She will put me up in my kennel and them I am a good quiet boy, because I can’t see her anymore.  I THINK she’s trying to teach me something, and I’m pretty dang smart she tells me, so I must be right!  I’m also learning the only other bad habit that I have is when I see her or the little human that lives with me, I JUMP, JUMP, JUMP!  She taught me to sit and said I learned it REALLY FAST, I think this must be to help me with the jumping, because whenever I JUMP she says SIT and I get a treat and a GOOD BOY when I do!   It’s pretty easy for me to train humans……  I DO have a lot of energy and like to RUN ( I was found running and running after all!) so I will need some humans that can take me on a lot of adventures, play with me and let me keep working on training them, good thing us young pups are around to do that, those older ones just don’t have the energy to be diligent at training their people!  Do you need some training that I can help you with?  Oh, one more thing.  My foster mom said she really loves me and doesn’t want me to be running out in the big scary world on my own again so please make sure you have a safe and secure yard for me to be in!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.CUDDLE ALERT! Hi! My names Sully and I'm looking for a home that enjoys three things: play time, snuggle time and nap time! I am a pretty easy going pup who loves attention! I love my new foster brother. He's a big pup just like me, as I have a high prey drive and only should be in a home with larger dogs and no cats. If he decides to stop playing though, I can get bored and decide to go on my own adventure, so I either need a long chain outside, or a tall fence that I can't climb. If I'm not playing with my foster brother, I am either enjoying my kong filled with treats and peanut butter or taking a nap next to my foster mom. My foster parents say that I am potty trained and have great manners! I don't beg for food, and I know sit, lay down and shake (this one is my favorite). My foster parents also say I am trying to work on my crate training. I like to 'talk' when I'm in my kennel and need a strong kennel so I can't escape. I am training on this and it is getting better! I'm not a chewer however, and most of the time I don't even need to be in it! I hope I find my forever family soon! My foster parents say my sweet personality and willingness to always give snuggles will give me an edge up on finding my forever family.

Sincerely,

Sully

Adoption fee includes: Full veterinary exam, alter, prepaid microchip, dewormed, Rabies vaccine, DAPP vaccine, Bordetella vaccine, 4DX

, flea/tick and heartworm preventative while in rescue. Adoption fee: $295.00

animal.description:
Tundra was surrendered due to a breeder downsizing their operation.  He was born April 7, 2018.  He was kept in a small pen with his mate, Gabby.  Tundra is a large boy and very friendly.  He has a calm and gentle temperament. He is fine with other dogs, and good with cats too.   He will benefit from some simple training.  Due to limited socialization, he is not used to a lot of sounds and experiences most dogs have.  He can be protective of his space.  Someone who can be patient with him, as he learns new things, would be best for him.  We recommend obedience training for all newly adopted pyrs, to help you create a special bond with you and your new friend, and so you have a well behaved canine. Great Pyrenees are willing to learn, but are not as eager to comply with commands as much as other breeds. They are bred to be independent thinkers. Applicants must be over 25, own their own home and all children in household must be over 6 years old. Your resident pets must be up to date on vaccines, sterilized, you must have a good history of vet care for them, and you must have used heartworm preventative year round for your dogs. 


Tundra will be placed as an inside pet with outside privileges. You MUST have a securely fenced yard accessible from your home. Invisible fencing does not work with this breed and they will take the shock for the freedom.  Great Pyrenees are bred to roam and will create their own territory if not secured, which can led to them being lost, hit by vehicles or shot by people who see them as a threat. The breed is not a good off leash dog, and cannot be trusted to not run away.  A Great Pyrenees off leash is a " DisAPyr." 

If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please complete the appropriate application on our website, www.igpr.org under the Adopt tab. 

All of our dogs marked as needing foster homes are also available for adoption.  If a dog is listed on this site, it is available.  No need to contact us to see if it is,  We do require you  complete the adoption application prior to meeting a dog.

We also offer a foster to adopt program. You foster the dog, and have first right of refusal on them if an approved application is submitted for them. 

In fostering a dog, the dog comes to you fully vetted. and groomed. You provide good quality food, grooming, and we provide the heartworm preventative and medical care, if needed* .(*Based on approval from IGPR.)

Adoption fee is $350.

Sage is dog selective, but leash reactive. She should be the only dog in her household.

Sage is not getting any applications because she is ugly. She is a soft, snuggly dog who will make you laugh every day. She has humble expectations of what a great life is!

animal.description:
Meet Buddy
Buddy and Dixie are bonded and will be adopted together.   These super sweet doggos, have no business in a shelter. We hope we can find them their forever home soon. They were dropped-off at a high-kill shelter when their family situation changed recently. We rescued them just as soon as we could. They arrived at our shelter on August 8, 2020. They are incredible and will fit into any home. The situation they are in now is really tough on them.   Let us tell you about them. 
Buddy is a retriever mix. He’s seven years old and weighs 62 lbs. Like his best mate, he’s also amazing. He’s calm, quiet, well-mannered, obedient, walks well on a leash, friendly, affectionate and so gentle. He’s most likely house-trained. We expect he’s dog friendly and we’ll test with cats for potential adopters. 
Dixie is a Beagle/Dachshund mix. She’s four years old and weighs just 25 lbs. She is incredibly sweet and gentle. Well-mannered, most likely house-trained. She is calm, quiet, walks well on a leash and welcomes any attention. Dixie is affectionate and friendly. She seems dog friendly, and we’ll test with cats for potential adopters.
We can’t say enough good things about Buddy and Dixie. Whoever had them before must have loved them a lot. These two do everything together and are very companionable. They are incredibly well-behaved and we can tell they just long to be in the quiet and safety of a home. They have become shelter favorites. They will make for incredible and loving companions. They’ve been through a lot, but are holding up like champs, always with a ready tail wag and doggy kisses. If you’re looking for two wonderful and easy-going dogs to open your heart and home to, Dixie and Buddy may just be the ones you’re looking for. 
Call 706-865-4135 for information on additional health services provided as part of the adoption fee.  If interested in one of our puppies or dogs, please submit an application online or at the shelter. Applications can be submitted online at: https://www.charlessmithgallhumanesociety.org/page/dog-adoption-application 
Once an application is submitted online, you will receive an email saying your application has been successfully submitted.  If you don’t receive this email within 24 hours, please check to make sure all application fields were completed or please call our shelter at 706-865-4135. All adopters must complete an approval process which involves a reference check with current/recent vet and a brief home visit if located in the immediate area. We do permit out of state adoptions. Adopters MUST come to the shelter to transport their new family member home. We do not ship nor do we transport them to their new homes. Adoption policies and application procedures are detailed at the shelter website: http://smithgallhumanesociety.org/ under tab All Adoptable Animals.
Charles Smithgall Humane Society (CSHS) is a No kill shelter. Animals in our care remain safe with us until adopted. Resident animals are primarily owner relinquished and also accepted from local Animal Control. The facility usually is operating at capacity with a list of animals waiting for space to open.
Adoptions and meet and greets are being scheduled by appointment only. Please call our office, email us or complete an application and someone will be in touch just as soon as they can. 
Location: 4823 Helen Hwy., Sautee, GA 30571, Phone: 706-865-4135
Email: smithgallhumanesociety@windstream.net
Our shelter in Sautee GA is located about 3 miles south of the alpine town of Helen in northeast GA.

They are incredibly well-behaved and we can tell they just long to be in the quiet and safety of a home. They have become shelter favorites. They will make for incredible and loving companions. They’ve been through a lot, but are holding up like champs, always with a ready tail wag and doggy kisses. If you’re looking for two wonderful and easy-going dogs to open your heart and home to, Dixie and Buddy may just be the ones you’re looking for. 
Call 706-865-4135 for information on additional health services provided as part of the adoption fee.  If interested in one of our puppies or dogs, please submit an application online or at the shelter. Applications can be submitted online at: https://www.charlessmithgallhumanesociety.org/page/dog-adoption-application 
Once an application is submitted online, you will receive an email saying your application has been successfully submitted.  If you don’t receive this email within 24 hours, please check to make sure all application fields were completed or please call our shelter at 706-865-4135. All adopters must complete an approval process which involves a reference check with current/recent vet and a brief home visit if located in the immediate area. We do permit out of state adoptions. Adopters MUST come to the shelter to transport their new family member home. We do not ship nor do we transport them to their new homes. Adoption policies and application procedures are detailed at the shelter website: http://smithgallhumanesociety.org/ under tab All Adoptable Animals.
Charles Smithgall Humane Society (CSHS) is a No kill shelter. Animals in our care remain safe with us until adopted. Resident animals are primarily owner relinquished and also accepted from local Animal Control. The facility usually is operating at capacity with a list of animals waiting for space to open.
Adoptions and meet and greets are being scheduled by appointment only. Please call our office, email us or complete an application and someone will be in touch just as soon as they can. 
Location: 4823 Helen Hwy., Sautee, GA 30571, Phone: 706-865-4135
Email: smithgallhumanesociety@windstream.net
Our shelter in Sautee GA is located about 3 miles south of the alpine town of Helen in northeast GA.

animal.description:
To be considered for one of our dogs, please fill out the online application on https://austinbulldogrescue.com/adopt/ 

ABR’s resident little lion Leo is a story in the perseverance of dogs. He was brought to us after being surrendered to a shelter in rough shape. Only 5 years old, he had advanced heartworm disease that had never been treated and was the victim of severe neglect. Despite his rough start to life, Leo is a wiggly ball of curiosity and love. His inquisitive eyes are always asking the same two questions: “Hey, watcha doing? Can I join?” Leo is fascinated with toys. He loves anything he can chase down and chew on (bonus points if it squeaks). While his heartworm disease makes it difficult for him to play for extended periods of time, he’s perfectly content to snuggle up next to you on the couch for an afternoon of TV and snuggles. But be warned, inviting Leo onto your bed at night is an invitation for him to lick your face and take up half the bed. If you’re looking for an adorable little bed hog who will give you unending love and an ever-wiggling tail, then this gentle soul will have you falling head over heels.

We are at an all time record for adopting or placing dogs with rescues as each dog spends an average 30-day stay at the shelter.  That’s pretty awesome!!!

In some cases, and for reasons beyond our understanding, some dogs get stuck for a while longer.  It's the case for our longest resident, Cooper, who has been with us since early August.  He is such a great boy, we don’t understand why nobody has snatched him up yet.  If you’re having a hard with how 2020 has been going and you need a pick-me-up, he is your boy.  Cooper is ALWAYS happy to be around his humans and would make a dedicated and faithful companion.  Just look at that face and heart-shaped markings.  Even though he hated the hat and is about halfway through his painful heatworm treatment (costs covered by Friends of Marshall County Animals), he still put on a smile for the pictures.  If you need happiness in your life, you need Cooper.  Please call Mary at 256-960-1408 to schedule a time to meet Cooper or help us share his story.

animal.description:
Please only send inquires to the email in this bio all others will not be answered. Please read the bio before sending questions - we answer all we know about the dog here.

Hi everyone...my name is Lillie - I'm a 5 yrs old American Bulldog. I weigh approximately 65 pounds. My family believes it's best for me to find a home I'm not as stressed out in... They weren't able to give me enough time and attention.

I am house-trained, spayed/microchipped, UTD on vaccinations and on flea/he preventative. My current family gives me cosequin also daily because my previous brother developed joint problems as he got older so they thought they would be proactive. They take really good care of me they just know it's best for me to find another home.

I'm a really loving girl and can't wait to find my new family. I'm cautious around new dogs I am a complete alpha I like to be the queen bee.

I've never been around cats and ok with mature older children

I will be your protector You will come to love me as I will love you. I do bark when somebody rings the doorbell or when somebody knocks on the door. I'm not a big fan of people wearing hats. They seem kind of weird to me. I'm also not a fan of cigarette smoking but you really shouldn't be either...It's not good for your health.

I really like food a lot I don't recommend you put your hands near my food dish... Sometimes I act like I've never been fed before. I'm crate trained and leash trained. I know some basic commands like sit, come, bed and no.

If you think I would be a good fit for your home and would like to make me your new fur kid please fill out the application on the Heidi's Legacy website.

HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

Lillie's adoption fee is $300 - obedience/behavior training is required

Obedience training is also required for all our pups. We understand with what is going on in the world that this may be a bit delayed. Please email us the completion certificate.

To apply to foster or adopt please fill out application at

www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

Thank you for completing the application. We are all volunteers and short on time, we will contact you back only if we have more questions or your application is approved and you will be invited to meet the dog. We apologize for not being able to answer everyone back.

For more information contact Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

DOGS are in Foster Homes. There is NO shelter.

**Our companions MUST live in your home as part of your family.**We do not transport.

**See our website for more information. www.HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

All communication is thru email so please be patient with us. We are all volunteers and work full time jobs and have families of our own.

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

ADOPTION PROCESS:

1. Complete this application
www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

***Everyone must submit an application - we only keep them on file for 1 month

2. Application background check, vet check, etc

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description:
C'mon babe why don't we paint the town... and all that Jazz! That's right it's Roxy heart here, looking for a new spot to lay out my tunes! I'm a sweet loving girl who rides a little lower on the energy scale! I do love dogs and even those dicey cats are cool! Walking and being your shadow that's my goal, though I'm probably best with older kids as my svelt 50lbs and happy go lucky demeanor can be too much for little ones! Im ever the lady on a leash and love a good cuddle at home! Who's ready to paint the town red and dance the night away? Or... watch movies and maybe drop a snack my way.

Roxy is a 3-year-old, 50-pound pit mix. She is UTD and spayed. She is housebroken and crate trained. Roxy has lived with dogs in the past but would do best with a slow intro. She likes cats and people but has never met young kiddos. Roxy does have severe allergies, however, her mom is in an emergency situation and is praying to find her forever home ASAP. 

Roxy doesn't understand why she can't stay with her current owner and has some anxiety. It will take a little patience (and treats certainly won't hurt) for her to warm up to her new family. Shes a sweet girl that is unsure of the world and needs to know its all going to be okay!

Adoption requirements are as such:


	Dog experience 


Please note, Roxy is part of Happy Trails Animal Rescues rehoming program. She has not been tested or evaluated and the information gathered is from the current owners personal statements regarding health and temperament. The owner is subject to placement outside of our organization. We cannot guarantee availability.

animal.description:
1/19/21 update: Magoo is doing very well in his foster home and enjoys sticking to his schedule. He is a vocal boy so an apartment would not be a good match as he might disturb the neighbors with his whining when he wants to go outside. He rarely barks. He enjoys going outside and being with his human. He is not a lap dog but likes to be next to his human and being pet. He is a very good and sweet boy. 

7/1/20: Magoo is a sweet older Chiweenie boy ~11 yrs old that was surrendered to us by from a domestic violence case.  His family loved him very much, but were unable to keep him so they reached out to see if we could help find a home for their special boy.  Magoo has hearing and some vision loss but loves to stay near his human and seems to find a way. He shys away from active dogs and activity in general, so he would do best with a quiet home and maybe a senior dog or two for him to retire in. He likes to lay near his human, but is not overly a lap dog. He does insist on following his human around the house or he will cry for your attention. He's housebroken, and sleeps in the bed against his foster mom... he will not jump off the bed due to mobility issues but will wake up his mom for assistance (normally because he is thirsty).  He enjoys short leash walks and likes to prance around.  He also likes to be carried, but can be a bit heavy at 12#. He is affectionate and likes to be petted and give kisses, but seems to have lost his bark. We want nothing more then to find this sweet older gentleman a home to call his own for whatever time he has left.  A reduced adoption donation of  $75 is being asked to cover a portion of his veterinary and care fees.  

He has been neutered, examined, treated for internal and external parasites, vaccinated and 4dx tested. For more information, please fill out an application from our website at allcreaturesbigandsmall.org or allcreaturesbigandsmall.petfinder.com!

Please copy and paste a completed adoption application from our homepage with your inquiry if you would like a response back. We get dozens of emails and phone calls each day with only an hour of "free time" to volunteer and answer them around our full-time jobs and family life...don't let your inquiry get passed by because of an incomplete application. Thanks in advance for your help!

Help our rescue by donating to our "Spay the momma fund". When adopting one of our babies, if each new family would contribute an extra $10 we can help out that babies mother by assisting with the cost of her spay. Help turn the momma into a pet rather than a breeding factory, donate today!

Adoptions limited to a 1 hour radius of Pulaski, NY and pets must be viewed in person by all family members prior to adoption; animals will not be shipped to their new homes. Veterinary reference check and adoption donation also required. Check out our homepage for a full list of our adoption requirements.

Augusta Dog Adoptions is an all- volunteer, foster- based rescue. We take applications online and are scheduling individual adoptions in the Waynesboro, VA area during the pandemic.  A $175.00 adoption fee ($300 for puppies under 6 months old) helps us take care of all the dogs we rescue. All dogs are spayed/neutered, tested for heartworm and tick borne diseases (if old enough), microchipped, and vaccinated for rabies (if old enough), distemper/parvo and bordetella. They are also treated for internal and external parasites. Many dogs also receive extensive medical care such as dental work and major surgeries. For more information and to apply to adopt, please visit www.augustadogadoptions.org

https://www.caninecastaways.org/adoption-application
IF A PET IS LISTED THEN THEY ARE AVAILABLE - WE KEEP OUR LISTINGS UP TO DATE AND REMOVE AS SOON AS ADOPTED.

NAME:  Pepper
BREED:  Chihuahua mix
SEX:  female
COLOR:  black
AGE:  10 yrs as of Aug 2020
WEIGHT:  9 lbs


FOSTERED BY: Nancy
LOCATED IN:  Arcadia


NOTES FROM FOSTER FAMILY:

Pepper is a very lovable girl.  She gets along great with other small dogs and cats. She loves to go for walks, look for squirrels and chase bugs. She also loves to pick out a comfy spot on the couch. She does well in a crate and does well in the house. She's  great with gentle kids and loves being petted.

It was obvious that Pepper had some allergy issues so we did all the testing to find out what was causing the problem.   She definitely cannot eat Chicken, duck or lamb in any form and is also allergic to storage and dust mites in addition to beet pulp.   

She is currently eating a fish based can diet but she could have some pork or beef in limited capacity since it is good to rotate foods/proteins around so that they get a variety of nutrients.  She CAN NOT eat any dry food or dry treats due to the fact that she is allergic to the storage mites - they are in all dry dog products.  This is a fairly common allergen and dogs with this allergy will need to eat canned, frozen food or could have home made balanced food as long as none of the items she is allergic to are in there.


Due to COVID-19 we are a little more limited on volunteers and the availability (and safety) of home visits.   Local applications are given first priority and some out of town areas will not be able to be processed.

At this time, we will only be able to process applications that have an excellent current vet history.  If you haven’t had a pet or verifiable vet history we will not be able to process your application.   


If you are interested in adopting please complete our Adoption Application by copying and pasting the following link into your web browser: http://www.caninecastaways.org/adoption-application

For a full list of dogs we currently have for adoption use this link:  https://www.caninecastaways.org/adoptable-dogs


MEDICAL INFO: 
The following has been or will be done for this dog...
- Basic Exam by Veterinarian
- Spayed or Neutered
- Heartworm Tested
- Placed on heartworm preventive
- Geriatric Bloodwork
- Microchipped
- Intestinal Parasite Exam and medication
- Vaccinations
- Placed on flea preventive
- Dental, if needed


ADOPTION DONATION: 
$150 

This adoption donation helps to cover the vet expenses for this dog including heartworm preventive which is dispensed at the initial vet visit and then goes with the dog at adoption. All vet records will be provided to adopter.


Visit us at www.caninecastaways.org

animal.description:
~Calling all Angel's! Molly's family's home suffered some extensive storm damage and is currently not livable. This sweet 11 year old pup Molly needs to be fostered while the dust settles or indefinitely.
Molly is a friendly girl but like many pitties is not great with other animals so is looking for a spot in a pet free home. Molly is up to date on her vetting and is healthy.

Please email us at AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com to find out if Molly is the right one for you! (Local adoptions preferred - Philadelphia and tri-state area [South Jersey and northern Delaware] only.)

PLEASE READ BEFORE CONTACTING US!
We are NOT a shelter: All of our dogs live in private homes with foster families. Come and meet the Almost Home dogs and their fosters at our Meet & Greet events, where you can learn more about our wonderful dogs from the people who live with them, find out which dogs are on their way and when they'll arrive, and fill out an application to adopt or foster.

We cannot adopt to homes where electric-shock fencing systems or training collars are used. For more information on the dangers of electric-shock collars, please visit banshockcollars.ca/studies.php and http://www.hollysden.com/say_no_to_shock.htm (scroll down and click on the "Invisible Fencing Systems" link).

We do not have an online adoption application; to request an application, e-mail us at AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com. To speed e-mail processing time, be sure to note the name of the dog you are inquiring about in the Subject line. For Meet & Greet times and locations, visit our home page, where you also will find information on our adoption process and fees.

FOSTER FAMILIES ARE LIFESAVERS!! Can you open your heart and home for a few weeks to homeless shelter dog? Remember, by fostering a dog, you save TWO lives - that of your foster dog, and that of the dog who takes his place in the shelter! Come to a Meet & Greet and find out if fostering is for you - there's no reward quite like the feeling that you've saved a life ... or two!

Marley is such a special puppy! At just 2.5 yrs. old, this handsome, smart, sweet, affectionate, Labrador/ Hound mix boy has been waiting patiently in his kennel at Rescue Ridge in Monmouth County NJ. He walks very nicely on a leash, takes toys, treats, food gently, keeps his kennel clean, and just needs an active family or person. Best in a home with older children because Marley might knock the little ones down. He needs an experienced owner who will keep up with his training, particularly with his leash grabbing antics which he thinks is a game. Marley likes to pick his doggie friends so if you have one we would have to see if he is a good match. He would be just as happy as your only pet. Marley is a great dog who clearly had someone love him at some point. Will YOU love Marley and take him home in time for the Holidays? animal.description:
Arlo is about two years old and came to us from Waukegan Animal Control. He came to us with kidney issues and is on medication to control it. Luckily, if you wrap his meds in cheese, he will gladly shake your hand for the honor of taking his meds. 

This guy really loves his humans and spending time with them! He will sit with you on the couch or play fetch with his favorite squeaky pig toy or happily walk with you to the ends of the earth. He is super smart and already knows sit and shake and is working on being comfortable in his crate. 

Arlo enjoys seeing other dogs on walks and greets them happily. He gets along with other dogs but would do fine as an only dog. He would do best in a home without cats or small children as he has exhibited a bit too much enthusiasm around cats and becomes protective around children. 

Black dogs often get overlooked, but one great thing about black dogs and Arlo in particular is that his shiny black coat stays shiny and black even after a roll around in the dirt!

This guy is a total lover! He looks like a croissant when he sleeps and has the craziest bark that sounds like he swallowed a whistle. He looks forward to taking his human on tons of adventures. If you’re interested in meeting Arlo, fill out a survey today at www.playersforpits.com/adoptionsurvey!

animal.description:
Buddy is a 2 year old bully breed, a pittie, - all that means is he is a mutt/mix!. He will love you with all his heart and wants to be the center of your attention as your only pet. He is an active dog who learns everyday. Did you know his foster home takes him almost everywhere? This guy has come a LONG way since he made it to EAPL. Shuffled back and forth we can only assume this boy had little stability. He is an active dog who would love to be the center of your attention, so no other doggies please. He's really not into cats either... If you are a kiddo, we prefer that you are over 10 years old. He is doing great in his foster home learning basic commands, manners and crate training. As you can see from one of these pictures - he LOVES to sunbathe!

Are you interested in a constant companion?

His adoption fee is $250 To meet this hunk, go to
www.eapl.com
and fill out an application.

Please feel free to contact the foster Mom if you have questions at 720-255-8812.

Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs.

Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please).  This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times.  

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details.
