COOKIE is a beautiful, 2-year-old, 45-pound Hound and Border Collie mix.

A smart "cookie", naturally independent girl.  Reserved around new people.  After her first week at the shelter, she's much more comfortable and relaxed with the staff.  

WHAT'S NEXT?

If you would like to meet, foster or adopt this pet, please fill out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - simply copy and paste the link into your browser. EASY PEASY!

Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you guys to meet! It'll be kind of like a blind date!

***

This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives.

Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. 

BY APPOINTMENT ONLY:  Meetings at our Adoption Center are by appointment only (no walk-ins).  An online adoption application is required and must be approved prior to meeting any animals.  Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please).  This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times.  

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details.

To fill out an adoption application, go to:
https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Berkeley - Male - ~10-years-old - #0800

Hello Berkeley! Our new boy Berkeley was found as a stray, fending for himself with the help of his buddy Bentley. The boys had been on their own for a while; we believe they were living together before being abandoned. Berkeley is adorable, only 40 pounds, with a very unique coat. Age hard to define so conservatively we are listing as 10-year old for both boys. Thankfully he tested heartworm negative. Ber
keley is very sweet, dog and cat friendly, rode great in the car, just snoozed with his pal. He is house and doggy-door trained. Berkeley had the normal neglect issues but also chronic ear infections and a wound we are treating. Berkeley definitely likes to be with humans, the shelter learned if left outside alone he can unlock the gate, a very smart boy who tells you what he wants.

Both Berkeley and Bentley are thankfully in the same foster home, thanks to an amazing Foster Family. We would love for the boys to be adopted together if at all possible.

If you are interested in adopting Berkeley or any GRRALL dog, please read our FAQs (https://grralliance.org/faq/) and submit an application at https://grralliance.org/applications/adoption-application/

GRRALL serves the Dallas-Fort Worth/North Texas area. We do not have the resources to adopt outside this region and do not ship dogs. If you are outside our adoption area please contact your local Golden Retriever Rescue, local independent adoption groups, shelters, humane society, or other group to find your perfect forever friend.

animal.description:
After being abandoned on the streets of Chicago, sweet senior Sofia found herself at the local city shelter. We sprung her out of there but her foster home couldn't keep her due to a management change. She is currently in boarding with some great people but Sofia is looking for a foster or adoptive home of her own. She would do best in a quiet home with no other pets. She can be a goofy girl and can knock over smaller kids but she'd love to have a teenager to hang out with. She is a lover and enjoys all the petting and scratches! 

Sofia loves rolling in the grass and soaking up the rays. Some days she's chill and other days she's silly. Even though she's an older gal, she's very spry and likes to bounce around sometimes. She loves to lean in to you for all the love.

She is housebroken, crate trained and great in the house. 

Can you help our golden girl enjoy her golden years?

Complete the application at www.cbbr.org!

animal.description:
Jasmine is an especially sweet female Weimaraner who came into our program after she was found as a stray.  Upon entering into our program, it was obvious that Jasmine has been neglected and has had many litters of puppies.

Jasmine is recovering and adjusting in a loving foster family and is ready to find her forever adoptive family.  She loves to play with the family's teenage children, is very gentle with everyone while doing that.  While her temperament is calm and laid back, she loves to go for leisurely walks, roll in the grass and smell the roses in her foster family's backyard,  Jasmine is housebroken and will do best in a quiet home where she will receive all the love and cuddles she so deserves.  While she gets along with her foster family's small dog, she would do best in a home without other big dogs or cats.

If you are interested in adopting sweet Jasmine and would like to learn more about her, please send us an email at contact@weimaranerrescue.org .  We are happy to communicate with you by email before asking you to submit an online application form.

animal.description:
http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html

Thank you so much for looking into wags and whiskers for your next family member.

All of our pets are up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested if over a year old and will be spayed or neutered before being allowed to go home.

Unfortunately, we don't always know the background of each dog. Some were dumped, abandoned in an empty house, left tied to a tree, picked up by animal control as strays, or simply unwanted by their owners. We ask that only serious and committed adopters apply as these dogs have suffered enough.

If you are interested in meeting this pet please apply to adopt at
http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html
if the pet is still available for adoption and you are approved to adopt we will contact you.

Calling and checking the status of your application will not increase your chances of adoption

animal.description: Mack and Mama have had a rough start to their lives. Mama belonged to a man who became homeless and he kept her with him even though he was a senior living on the streets. Unfortunately Mama became pregnant and she had Mack. For the last two years they have been living under a semi truck in a business where the owner let them be security. Unfortunately the owner of Mack and Mama had to leave town. Mama is actually very well rounded and sweet but Mack has only know living under a truck for the 1 year of his life and he was actually abandoned their by himself for several months so he was frightened to new surroundings. Now that he has been reunited with Mama he is doing great but right now he does need to stay with Mama. Adoption fee is $200 for the pair. We would love to find a real home for these sweet dogs. They do great with other dogs and people although Mack may be frightened of children at first. Please contact AdoptAnimalNetwork@gmail.com

animal.description: Oh hai, Manchego here! Just hanging out, looking handsome, doing what he does best! Manchego was in a foster home for several months and we learned ALL the things about him! He LOVES being with humans. and is very much a velcro dog. Manchego is well-behaved inside the house - he knows he has to wait to be invited on the couch, and he will wait adorably and patiently until you invite him. Manchego is house trained, crate trained, and very quiet - he rarely barks. He is also a quick learner and has mastered sit, shake, rollover, high five, lie down, and go to bed. (Check Manchego out in action here: https://youtube.com/watch?v=mC-T6w-9Ih8) Manchego is an affectionate, sensitive dog... cuddles are his favorite! He thinks he is a lap dog, and once he fully trusts you, he will try to give you one of his famous Manchego hugs. He also takes treats gently... peanut butter is his favorite, nom nom! Manchego is easily startled by joggers, cyclists, and scooters, so he'd prefer a lower-traffic area so he can enjoy his walks. Manchego's ideal home would be adult-only, quiet, and have a fenced yard. He is fearful of other dogs so he needs to be the only pet for now. The Orange Dot Crew (a volunteer advocacy group at Austin Animal Center) will be there every step of the way to make sure that Manchego is set up for success! I weigh approximately 62 lbs. Click here to view my behavior notes.

animal.description:
UPDATE - Winston was adopted in August and returned because he needs training. He can be jumpy on people and has has accidents in the house.

WINSTON - 2 years old, 60 pounds, house trained, good with kids, cats, dogs, a snuggler, very high energy, loves to run and play, always by your side.

Winston ended up in the Virginia Beach Animal Care and Adoption Center along with his sister, Nala, after their family got military orders to move to Japan. The dogs were with this family for a while now although both are still young. Winston is a player. He loves to play. He has very high energy and will definitley need lots of daily activity including exercise, playtime, and attention. He is the dog who will follow you around. You go to the kitchen, he will go to the kitchen. You run upstairs for a blanket to snuggle under while watching Netflix, he will run upstairs following at your heels and then he'll be that dog who will snuggle with you on the sofa. Winston is a friendly boy who will take lots of your time so if you enjoy free time and not having to answer to anyone, you might want to try another dog. Winston is a lover and a leaner. He is already house trained and good with everyone! Bring your crew in to meet him and let's see if we have a good match! Remember just because a meet and greet goes well at the shelter, chaperoning at home is vital to the successful integration of a new dog into a home. Winston is available for appointments; call 385-4444 or go to our Facebook page to make that appointment. Thanks for choosing adoption!

animal.description:
Requirements - Secure fenced yard and gate, young active adult ONLY home, no apartment. Applications from Chatham only will be reviewed.  Lucy and Winston are a bonded pair and will NOT be separated.

Lucy (brown/tan) is a 2 yr (DOB 2018) old little girl who is very shy with new people and can be a barker with new people.  She can nip if she feels threatened therefoere several visits with a portial adopter is a MUST.  She loves her little buddy Winston and loves to play fetch with her toys.  As long as  you are willing to throw, she is willing to run and fetch.  Once she knows you she is very loving and a good girl.  She is like a big sister to her buddy Winston.  

Winston is a 1 yr old (DOB 2019) long hair chi boy who is so loving!  He is high energy too!  He is always on the move and loves his big sister Lucy.  This little guy has to kiss, kiss, kiss as long as you let him.  He is also very very fast so extra precaution is a MUST to keep him safe.  He and Lucy get into tug of wars with toys.

This little couple came to our rescue when their owner passed away. They have never been around children.  They are very bonded and together at all times.  They love to run and having a secure fenced yard with no escape routes and gate are a MUST.

Because Lucy is very shy with new people, we will do more than one visit to help her feel comfortable.  Winston loves everybody!

These two are adorable and will bring so much joy to the family they choose.

Adoption Fee - $800

Please submit adoption application here - www.ckanimalrescue.com

animal.description:
My name is Ginger. I am a gorgeous little red headed angel....but sometimes my halo may get a little bit tilted....BUT DON'T let that stop you from coming to see me because we really could become the best of friends. I get along with some dogs, I just am dog selective. I also hear that some hooomans are the same way with other hooomans. I just need a home that will give me a chance to be your best friend. I have so much to offer the right family! So much love! I just haven't been shown it a lot in my past, until I moved up here to WI and met these great hooomans at the Forest County Humane Society. They showed me its ok to let my guard down and that all hooomans are not bad! Once I see that you are one of the good hooomans, I will love you forever and do anything I can to show you how big of a heart I have. If you want to go for a walk with me, please call the FCHS so they can talk to you about meeting me. They understand me, so I trust these hooomans will help me. Please let them help you too! Please give me a chance! You won't be disappointed! 
If you would like to see a video of me please go to http://bit.ly/AdoptableDogVideos
SL # 268240For best response to an inquiry about this animal, please visit www.forestcountyhumanesociety.org, fill out an application and return it to us. Thank you!

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Paco!

I'm a 19-month-old American Staffordshire Terrier. My foster mom says I'm the sweetest Staffie she has ever fostered (and she has fostered many). Inside the house, I'm very polite. I've already got a bunch of commands (sit, stay, leave, place...) down. I'm not possessive with my food, toys, nor my bed, and I only do my "business" outside the house. I also never bark! I usually go along with the rhythm of the household. If everybody is out working I will patiently wait and chill but oh boy, if they get back home and they want to play, I'm ready to give it my all.

My foster mom also says I'm a great cuddle buddy. We can just veg out and watch movies together on our couch. I'm very friendly with humans and any visitors that come to the house. My only downside is that I'm reactive to other dogs when walking on a leash. I need someone very strong and attentive to keep up with me. The good thing is, I've been training with an E-Collar and it seems to be working out great.

I can't wait to find my forever home. Ideally, my dream home would be a home with energetic and adventurous adults and maybe some teenagers to play with me and help me release some of my energy, and of course, a family that's willing to give me lots and lots of love, just like my fosters do.

Are you ready to receive Paco's love and affection?

If so, please submit a completed
adoption application found
at www.doggiebonez.com so that we can schedule a meet and greet. He is also on all of our social media pages IG: @Doggie_Bonez_Inc_ and Facebook: Doggie Bonez.

If adoption isn't an option, please consider fostering one of our pups. We are a volunteer-run non-profit dog rescue and always welcome new short or long-term doggie foster families. We much appreciate the help and time of our fosters. You provide all the love, comfort, and safety of a home, and we supply you with everything else you may need, dog food, dog bed, toys, medical attention (if required), etc. If you are interested, please visit www.doggiebonez.com to see all of our available dogs who need a foster family while waiting for their fur-ever home and complete the foster application.

animal.description:
Olivia is 1-2 years old and weighs not quite 40 pounds. She was born in open desert and survived thanks to the kindness of strangers who left food and water on a daily basis. We were able to catch Olivia, her brother Oliver (aka Ollie) and their mother. A TOUGH CATCH! They are wholesome, healthy and sociable with other dogs. Her adoption fee is $450 which covers the cost of her spay, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), flea & tick medications, microchip and microchip registration. If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application, available on our website, poochmatch.com, under the adoption tab and please read the paragraphs below for more details on our process.

If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for him/her. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

UPDATE: ADOPTION EVENTS CANCELLED DUE TO PANDEMIC AND SOCIAL DISTANCING. If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog at our weekly adoption event on Saturdays at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda, CA (5521 Mirage St.) between 1-5 PM, please fill out an application from our website, poochmatch.com, and submit it no later than 11 AM on Fridays. Upon receipt AND approval, the dog you are interested in meeting will be made available to meet on a Saturday. Due to the high volume of dogs and puppies in our foster homes, it is impossible to bring them all every Saturday. The only way to ensure that the dog that you are interested in will be at the adoption event is to FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AND BE APPROVED. Otherwise, we cannot guarantee that the dog you are interested in will be at our adoption event. If you cannot make the time frame of our events, appointments can be made at another time and location solely at the discretion of the foster parent. Please understand that private appointments will be coordinated to meet the convenience of the foster parent/transporter. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $225-$495.


COVID-19 PROCEDURE:
In an effort to create a safe environment for our potential adopters and our staff, we have changed our protocols and procedures during these difficult times. Starting immediately, our procedures will change from what’s written on our website and other social media platforms. Our weekly adoption event at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda is temporarily cancelled due to COVID-19 and social distancing. The only way to meet one of the dogs/puppies we have available for adoption is through completion of our adoption application through our website, poochmatch.com, before 11 AM on Fridays. On Fridays when we review the applications, we will pick the best fit for each dog or puppy applied for and coordinate mutually agreeable appointment times for the applicants who are approved that week. Private appointments are currently only scheduled on Wednesday, Thursday or Saturday of each week. Masks or bandanas are mandatory; faces must be properly covered.

With the overwhelming desire of the public to adopt at this time, we have received as many as 30 applications for one dog in just one week. Working with a staff of volunteers, we are only able to reach out on Fridays to the people we have approved to adopt. If you have not heard from us by Friday, we have selected a different applicant. If you have multiple dogs/puppies that you are interested in, please indicate each dog/puppy of interest on the application at that time so we don’t rule you out for another dog/puppy available for adoption.

Please understand, we have an influx of texts, phone calls and emails that makes it impossible to get to each and every one of you. Not just for adoption interest, but also from veterinarians, people who must relinquish dogs, people who have found a stray dog in need of pick up, etc. We are currently not in need of fosters. Due to the fact that there is such a high demand, we are sticking with strict protocol to not adopt out of Southern California. We apologize for this inconvenience and difficulty to be able to get in touch with us while there is an overwhelming desire and demand to adopt at this time. We appreciate your understanding and patience as we navigate through these difficult times with every intention to keep the public and our staff safe.

animal.description:
One of a pair of hybrid type fellows who arrived via a small rescue in the Sacramento area. Cysco is smaller and likely perhaps to be part Coyote. These are truly delightful creatures, playful and silly, who just love romping and playing in the wooded hills at our Sanctuary! They have two delightful girlfriends in their pack and the foursome immediately took to each other like long lost friends (or family members!) Cysco is not a dog who chooses human company, though he is sweet, sensitive, curious and does engage, but chooses dogs over humans. We respect that choice and give him and the others the time and a big space to call home - eventually in the right circumstances with the right kinds of people and other dog(s) we can consider placing them, or they'll stay here and have their friends and good food and a happy life!

Thank you for considering adoption of a Milo Foundation Sanctuary dog.
Our Sanctuary is where our rescued dogs who have had difficulty in a home in the past, have behavioural issues, or too much energy, or for some, aggression issues with other dogs, or intense stranger danger that make them more difficult to safely and happily live in urban environments.
These are not beginner dogs or for the most part nor are they for families with children. IF you are looking for an easy dog to add to your family, we suggest looking at the dogs at our Adoption Center, Milo Pt Richmond. 
BUT, if you can offer a safe and nurturing home to a dog with some behavioural "quirks" please do send an application today. Thank you.

animal.description:
Gable is a little over a year and a half old and very handsome. He LOVES water. He will splash in a kiddie pool or get in a stream or pond happily. He can play with other dogs supervised. He's not aggressive but he plays hard. A big dog who also plays hard would be best if there is another dog but he needs guidance on what is appropriate. He's a bit rambunctious with cats- barks and tries to play with them so that may not be a good idea.

He is young with a high energy level. He loves to play fetch. He would make a great hiking buddy or running buddy (he can run really fats it's quite impressive). Even just a nice long walk would be okay with him. He will need daily exercise. He is food motivated so highly trainable and very smart. If he's had his play time or walks, he will absolutely be happy to cuddle up with you or lay down in his crate to chew on a bone. He is crate trained and goes in on command. It's his safe place to relax. He is house trained and also knows a doggy door. He has never chewed on anything he shouldn't. He sits and waits nicely for his food.

He does have some leash manners but can be distracted by bunnies and birds when out walking. He is scared of new people who come into his home so he would need a low traffic home that doesn't have a lot of visitors. His humans need to understand that he needs time to get used to new people at his own pace and not to force it. Once he's bonded to his humans, he loves them with all of his heart and wants to be loved in return. He adores kids. 

Because Gable has bully characteristics, BSL restrictions will apply. Must own home & cannot live in a breed restricted area.

Estimated DOB: 1/10/19

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Please review our Adoption Process before filling out an application. If you would like to try a Foster to Adopt trial, please fill out an Adoption Application.

If you are only interested in temporarily Fostering one of our rescues, please fill out a Foster Application.

Meet Betty! UPDATE 1-17-21 : Betty was adopted in September 2020 and sadly, her family has relinquished her back to ARWOB. This was not Betty's fault, as her adopter stated that the family realized they are not ready to have a dog. They feel she would be better off with a family that can give her more attention and who has a bigger home with a yard. Here is what they have to say about Betty: 'I cannot emphasize what a great pup she is. Overall she is house trained, but occasionally will chew on a sock, sandal or a cord (but the cord thing was our fault because we should have kept it out of reach). She will use the pee pad when the family is home with her, but she will hold it when we leave her alone. When she is home alone, she has access to the pee pad, but does not use it often. The longest she has been home alone is 5 hours. She sleeps at night in her crate without issue. However, she naps in the day on my son's bed or sofa chair. She just loves children and other dogs. She can sometimes be skittish around bigger dogs, but then she warms up after a while. We have traveled (by car) outside of San Diego county and she does great in car rides. And I am impressed how she is not a barker. She will occasionally bark but it's never continuous. We have taught her to 'sit' in Spanish and she will listen to 'stay' unless she gets really excited. We have her on a regular walking schedule of 3-4 times a day so she gets her exercise.' ORIGNINAL RESCUE STORY :
Betty is an adorable terrier mix, who was rescued off the streets of Tijuana in early July and is a great little pup! Betty will likely be full grown in the 20-25 pound range as a typical small breed mix. Like all pups, she is very outgoing and will need an adopter who is willing to enroll her in dog training classes. She is already crate trained and is getting the hang of house training. She is not a very vocal small breed dog, which is great. She loves dogs, cats and kids. She is very sweet and a little nervous when first meeting new people, but quickly relaxes. Betty is scheduled to be spayed on 9/4 in the San Diego area, and as such we prefer adopters who are local to San Diego, as it will be a requirement for her adopters to be able to drive Betty to and from her spay appointment. Betty is ready to go home as soon 8/1 The meet and greet will be scheduled in the 92117 area and we are accepting applications now. Please submit online at www.arwob.org Don't wait...Submit an adoption application today! If you would like to meet one of our animals, PLEASE fill out an adoption application.

please fill out a short questionnaire in addition to the adoption application.

animal.description:
Say hello to Maia. She still has a few quirks from spending time in boarding but she is very affectionate and a great dog!! Maia loves to spend time outside, thinks she's a lap dog and enjoys treats (especially cheese). When we get home Maia greets us with excitement and her tail wagging to the point her whole backside shakes. Maia is much better walking past animals during her long walks but she needs to be the only pet in her new home. Maia needs a family that will be patient as she adjusts. This little lady let's you know she wants attention by pushing her nose into your hand for some petting and affection. She will also roll over and enjoy a good belly rub when you're willing to give one. Maia likes to play with toys and her teenage foster brother even taught her to fetch. Although she doesn't always give it back. You should definitely make plans to meet this beautiful, 5yr old Kelpie mix in hopes of adding her to your family. 60lbs Born around 2016. 

Adoption fee is $175 and includes DHPP & rabies vaccinations heartworm testing spay/neuter surgery deworming and microchip. All animals are examined by a veterinarian. Please fill out our application at https://gkarma.wufoo.com/forms/good-karma-pet-rescue-dog-adoption-screening/; if you are interested in meeting or adopting this dog and we will be in touch right away!

animal.description:
BIRDIE, FEMALE, 1 YEAR OLD, 50 POUNDS

BIRDIE IS BEING FOSTERED IN THE RICHMOND VA AREA. IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN BIRDIE, PLEASE GO TO WWW.MOMSVA.ORG AND COMPLETE AN APPLICATION. 

They call me Birdie…well my foster parents sometimes call me "Birdieroo" because I can jump so high they think I must be part kangaroo!  I've finished my heartworm treatment and have even gone through formal e-collar training. I know several commands and my foster Mom is continuing to work with me using positive reinforcement techniques. I'm doing a great job. I'm just really smart and full of energy so sometimes I need help focusing. My new person and/or family will need to commit to continuing to work with me on my manners. I do very well in my crate as long as I get enough exercise when I am out and I've never met a squeaky toy or person that I don’t love to play with. I'm looking for an active home that can keep me busy but the most important thing to me is to be able to be around my people who I love to cuddle with on the couch, watching t.v., at the end of the day.  

I get super excited around other dogs so the great folks at MomsVA think I would do best as an only dog or in a home with a young, very playful, middle- to large-sized male dog. My forever home should not have cats as I have a very strong prey drive. I’m kinda bouncy, so young children would not be best right now because I might accidentally knock them over in my excitement.  

Even after my rough start in life, I am still full of joy and silliness. I make my foster family laugh every day!  If you are looking for a loyal and loving furry family member and think we could be a match,  go to www.momsva.org and complete an application.

animal.description: This fine lady is Linda! Linda is a young adult (probably around 2 years old) and she's an Anatolian Shepherd. Linda's trying on her holiday outfit, and we must say she looks smashing!!! Linda has been with us for a while now, and we are committed to finding Linda the wonderful home that she deserves! Some info on Linda: she was found as a stray and it was discovered that she had an old injury that required surgery and removal of her leg. Linda stayed with us through her surgery and rehab, and she's adjusted quite well to her "new normal" (2020 was "a year" for everyone!). Linda loves her people and she did have a stint in a foster trial, where we learned that she is SO excited about other dogs, that she needs a handler who can help channel that excitement. We've worked with Linda to socialize her and give her lots of positive experiences with dogs, and she has made a number of doggy friends here. The challenge is actually limiting her play, since her one hind leg can only handle so much (she's a very large girl, so her handlers must be mindful as Linda would easily over do it!). Linda is only around 2 years old, and we think she's an Anatolian Shepherd (or mix). Linda needs a home with no cats, and preferably some non-slip floors! Due to her size and need for continued socialization, we think she'd do best in an adult only home. If you have the experience and time to devote to this sweet girl, please send us a message today!

animal.description:
(Version française disponible ici: 
https://www.sitwithme.ca/fr/dogs/sprite/ ) 


Sprite

American Bulldog / Terrier mix

1,5  year

Female

 

Dogs: Yes to a friendly, similar sized and non-confrontational (playful) dog. Meet and greet near Ottawa required.

Cats: Not sure, we will update when we know but for now, no.

Kids: No, thank you.  She actually is friendly with kids but a kid-free home life is needed (keep reading).

Housing: Detached only – no attached housing!

Fenced-in Yard: Required  or a private country setting where she would be always supervised (ie. never left out alone) on a long line could work too instead of a fence!

Special Needs: Sprite has separation anxiety.  We have discovered that an empty room with an open crate and lots of puzzles and bones does the trick!  She can now be left successfully but we are looking for a home where someone is home more often. To apply, you must have a designated room in the home for this muffin.

*Sprite has bully features and as such, we will only place her within Ottawa or outside of Ontario within 2 hours of Ottawa where there is no breed specific legislation.  She needs a meet and greet before being matched and so the home must be within driving distance.*



Sprite is such a sweet dog.  She loves deeply and is an obliging cuddler, if you will have her.  She is smart, eager to please and super cute.  She loves to go for long walks and while she pulls initially in excitement, this quickly lessens as she heads out for her 4km walk.  Yes, this gal loves to play, loves to investigate, loves to go on adventures and would love a dedicated human to continue the great work her foster mom has started.  She’s looking to be someone’s heart-dog and we know she has all the makings to be exactly that for her future person/couple, but she still has work ahead, so keep reading!

 

When meeting new people, treats go a long way.  Sometimes she will bark if she is unsure, but she can easily be won over with kindness and FOOD!  That sweet wiggle butt of hers is the best! Food is a great tool to encourage this gal to be brave in a sometimes overwhelming world.  Forced handling or loud voices can overwhelm Sprite and so this delicate flower (she’s really not that delicate) would love someone who will encourage her in life.  

 

Sprite is a playful and sometimes over-exuberant as a canine play buddy.  She never means anything malicious by her rough or excited play, but this is why it is important that any dog in the home is non-confrontational.  She does not share food or toys well with other dogs and so while we believe she would love having another playful dog in the home, the toys/bones/food will need to be properly managed (put away when both dogs are out).  She may be okay with cats based on her shelter assessment but we have not yet tested her.  Hopefully we can do so soon.

 

When she is over-aroused (often when her person comes home), she does not manage that excitement boost well.  She then becomes “nippy”.  She is not trying to be difficult or aggressive, but she does need to be let outside and ignored until she calms down on her own.  This is why small kids in the home are not ideal even though when she is calmer, she does well to say hello and hang out.  This behaviour will need to be managed calmly and as such, she will need a dedicated human to work with her to be the best girl she can be.

 

Sprite struggled with crate training due to a neglectful past.  We worked very hard to find a solution because Sprite was such a sweet girl and we did not want her past to define her.  We discovered after working through many options, that having an empty room for her, along with an open crate with a blanket, a few bones, a few toys and some treat puzzles was the solution!  She now happily runs to her room when her foster mom has to head out and can be left for hours at a time without an accident.  Of course, she does get stressed which is why we are hoping to find someone that works from home, works shorter days at the office, or only works a couple of days a week instead of the usual 5. 

 

Sprite is the most endearing, beautiful, dedicated, loving and cuddly gal a person can ask for but she also needs some help to be the best girl she can.  She has a super wiggle butt, will happily share your bed at night and keep you safe from all of the monsters underneath, and gives pretty great kisses too.  If you have the dedication to be this girl’s forever person, please complete an application here: http://www.sitwithme.ca/Sprite

animal.description:
Lily is absolutely the bees knees!! A true diamond in the RUFF! One year ago Lily was picked up as a stray in Wichita, KS, obviously a new momma (just a baby herself), taken to a kill shelter where she was euth listed due to fear - sadly her puppies were never looked for or found. Thankfully, a rescue stepped up to save her life with moments to spare. 
Lily is estimated to be just over a year and a half, still a boisterous youngster, FUN, full of energy, and eager to please! Sadly, Lily had a rough start in life and quickly learned that humans aren't always kind, which has led to some trust issues and feeling she needs to be protective of her space - but once she trusts you, she's an absolute JOY! 
Because of this, Lily needs an experienced adopter, willing to go slow and respect her boundaries to build trust, someone that can be a strong leader with a gentle hand to help her continue to shine like the diamond she is. She is smart as a whip, corrects easily with words, and can pick up on tonal cues - plus she's VERY food motivated! 
Lily can be selective about her doggie friends, as she has some alpha tendencies, but truly enjoys the company of a social submissive canine companion that doesn't make her feel challenged/threatened. She would do best paired with a playful canine who can show her the ropes of being a dog and help her blossom. 
**No cats - as she has a high prey drive.**
**No young children - as she can be mouthy when over stimulated, or reactive if startled/feels threatened.**
Lily LOVES walks, belly rubs, bones, rides in the car, and "killing" toys, but her most favorite pastime is digging up rocks in the yard. She's quite the amateur geologist and has a fantastic collection!!
Like all young dogs, Lily will benefit from a healthy exercise regimen (jogging partner?) and continued obedience training. She does pull on leash and can be reactive if she sees another dog or small critter that needs to be chased - but she is getting better! Lily is house broken and knows "kennel," "treat," "come," "sit," "down," "off," "paw," & "sit up." We are currently working on "heel," "drop it," & "stay." Come meet Lily!! We promise she will steal your heart!! ?

animal.description:
Eve's Sanctuary does not have a public location to visit, although we do weekly adoption events in public locations on the UWS. If you are interested in a specific animal, please email info@evessanctuary.com with the name of the animal you are interested in written on the subject line. Please remember that ESAR requires a full complete application, an interview, and a home visit prior to final approval and placement of adopted animals. It may seem daunting at first, but to find true love its worth it, right? They aren't products on a shelf to buy, we love them like our own, and only want the best possible home for each and every one...thus the "hoops." Also, please trust our recommendations, we are skilled human furry freind matchmakers with many years of experience that has given us a unique and solid perspective. For these reasons we prefer adopters to be in NYC or the immediate area accessible by public transportation so we can work with you individually and educate you face to face!
Additionally, please understand that we are all volunteers, no salaries are paid, we have families and pets of our own, and we have full time jobs in addition to doing rescue work - so we may be (at times) slow-ish to get back to you. We promise we are doing our best as its in everyones best interest to place these darlings quickly, so we can save more. If you would like to expedite the process, and make us extra happy, please download our application from our website at: http://www.evessanctuary.org/Adoption.html , fill it out, and return it with your initial email inquiry. Be patient, be persistent, be polite, and we promise all will be well! ;-)
All animals come up to date on annual combo vaccs, rabies vaccs, heartworm tested negative, microchipped, and of course...spayed or neutered!

animal.description:
IN VERMONT
/ IN NEED OF LOCAL FOSTER OR ADOPTER/ AVAILABLE FOR FOSTER TO ADOPT FOR LOCAL ADOPTERS

Meet Rocco! Here is his video collage in NC & SC:
https://youtu.be/5ym6uYdr5GY

Rocco is 5 years old (approx. DOB 6-26-15), male, 52 lbs., vetted, is or will be neutered, and micro-chipped. This handsome poor boy was found homeless in the road trying to do a "self surgery" in NC and dragging a hanging pendulas cannonball tumor (since surgically removed). A good Samaritan stopped and picked him up to bring him to the shelter for help. Then June 3rd happened when our Founder happened to be making an in person visit to the shelter to help some dogs. As soon as she saw Rocco she knew he stood little chance of making it out as no one would want to take on the medical bills. The P4P Community stepped up and contributed to help us Rescue him and cover medical bills! He is doing great now as you can see! He is a sweet boy that assessed well with other dogs; he can't wait for his new furever home!

Stay tuned for more information as Rocco is a new rescue!

If you are interested in fostering or adopting Rocco please fill out an Application at
www.Passion-4-Paws.org
(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out his Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description: Oak IS AVAILALBE (updated 02-02-2021).To meet any of our dogs you must first complete our online adoption application on our website. For more information and the adoption application for Oak, please visit our website belowhttp://www.coastalgsr.org/dog_profile.php?ID=22313&name=OakOaks never met a person he didnt think loved him more than French fries and would have no problem asking strangers for attention and affection. Hes super smart, knows his basic commands, is good on a leash, and eager to work for food. Around 1-2 years old, Oak loves his walks and has been good with everyone he's met. Leash walking seemed fairly new to him when rescued, but hes mastered that task. All Oak dreams of is an active home who can provide him with the structure a young pup needs so that he'll grow up to be a respectful, happy boy who will continue spreading his joy all over Southern California. Oak wasn't previously socialized with other dogs and doesn't do well with them. Because of this, he needs to be the only dog in the household and isnt compatible with apartment living. The minimum adoption donation for adults is $375 and the adoption donation for puppies is $500. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is tax deductible. The adoption donation provides that all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis ( i.e., puppies who will need to be altered by 6 mos old). Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

animal.description:
My name is Sugar Bee and I am healed and ready for my new home. I am a husky/lab mix and I weight approximately 50 lbs. I LOVE to run if I am not contained. I like to go for walks/ short runs and to just relax and soak up the sunshine. The vet thinks I am 4.5 years old according to my teeth, but I am still full of energy and love to run and play. I love to snuggle and get attention. I do have some minimal medical needs that the great people who saved me can discuss with you if you choose to make me a member of your family. I will be spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and HW negative with monthly preventatives upon adoption. If you are interested in giving me a great forever home (fenced yard required) please clink on the link below to directions to the adoption process and the application.

www.savingdogsrescue.com/how-to-adopt

My story, I was hit by a car in February of 2020 and taken to the local animal shelter where I was evaluated at the local vets and determined that I would need extensive operations and rehab to survive. The local animal rescue pulled me from the shelter and took me to the vet. At that time they operated to repair the hole in my bladder. After a week or so of rest then I was stable enough to have my pelvic bones surgically repaired. I then spent 4 months on cage rest with rehabilitation 3 times a day to get my hind legs working and to help my bowels and bladder to start working again. I have now been able to use the restroom on my own and run and play with very minimal change. So now I am ready to find a home to call my own.To access our online adoption application copy and paste the url into your browser: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=zw1754&method=online_form_html&formid=41

animal.description:
My name is Spinner, I am Chihuahua mix, male, 4 1/2 years old and weigh 12 lbs. 

The odds were stacked against me early in life, but then my previous mama found me and gave me a  happy, loving forever home.   Unfortunately, my mama passed away unexpectedly and now I need a soft place to land that will understand and be patient with my needs. A family who will love me and make my world feel safe again.  

I am 95% blind, but I am able to see shadows. We believe this is caused by a neurological condition that also seems to make learning more difficult but with consistency I am able to learn new things. 

I spin a lot (hence the name). I tend do this when I am scared or stressed, but I also do it to figure out my location. I love my food so much that I get very upset if my food bowl is empty!  I use the words food bowl “lightly” because I really like to just dump it out and eat it off the floor very slowly so I can savior the taste. I am not fully potty trained but my foster mom is working really hard with me!  I have lived with other dogs and my foster home has dogs and we all get along fine. I am not sure about cats, they are pretty sneaky and scary when you don’t know where their at!  Having someone pick me up can be really scary and sometimes I will scratch you out of fear. Maybe we could come up with a code of some sort to let me know you want to hold me?  My foster mom says I am a very happy boy and laps are the very best place to be. 

Wags thinks I would do best in a home with blind dog experience, a quiet home with other dogs and kids older than 12 that understand my special needs. I will need a securely fenced yard so I do not get lost. 

If you think Spinner may be the one for you, please go to our website at www.wagstorichesanimalrescue.org and fill out an application to adopt.  Please be sure to include a vet reference as regular vet care is important to us for the health of all our adopted dogs. With approval and a $295 adoption donation, he will be ready to accompany you on all of life’s many adventures.  Spinner is neutered, microchipped, fecal tested clean of internal parasites and up to date on all his vaccinations.

animal.description:
IN VERMONT

Meet Pixie fka Twinkie! More pictures and video to come!

Pixie is almost 3 years old (approx. DOB 10-10-16), female, 15 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed, and micro-chipped. Pixie was found homeless in NC and brought to the shelter. Pixie is good with other dogs, likes to ride in the car, does have a prey drive toward smaller animals so cats probably not a fit nor small children running around, she is house trained, and has medium+ energy. She like to be with her humans, She loves to run, loves to sleep on soft bed and blankets, loves treats, loves to snuggle, loves to have her own space, she likes to chew her toys, Pixie knows Sit, Come, Off, and Go to your Room! Pixie's best home would be active for her energy, have another dog (she'll do her best and be her happiest), no young children (the make her nervous and stressed), and where her humans would love her furever! At her current caretaker's there are a 1 year old and 3 year old children which Pixie is too stressed and not happy there. Stay tuned for more information as Pixie is a new rescue!

If you are interested in adopting Pixie please fill out an Application at www.Passion-4-Paws.org (please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.special_needs_notes:
We recently found out that Draco has a collapsed trachea.  He is also experiencing occasional seizures.  We believe the two are related, but are not certain.  

He is on two herbal supplements to strengthen his trachea.  Unless he experiences future seizures, our veterinarian does not feel the need to prescribe anti-seizure medications.

Draco will need someone who will not require him to perform strenuous exercise, but will play with him some, and will veg out with him as well.  

He is a wonderful dog, and, with the right home, will flourish!

animal.description:
Meet Apple.  

Apple has an interesting story.  We rescued her from her owner who kept her in a crate in his tool shed.  He had her since birth, but had never played with her, loved on her, or showed her any attention at all, other than feeding her.  Therefore, she is very shy until she warms up to you.  Warming up doesn't take long ( a couple to a few days), but she needs that time to learn she can trust you. She is very sweet!

She is up-to-date on all her vaccinations, but because she was never vaccinated as a puppy, she will need a distemper booster in a couple of weeks.  She had worms, but has been dewormed and will simply need a fecal retest in a few weeks to be sure she is worm free. 

She needs someone who will be patient with her and allow her to trust them.  She is very loving, she just simply needs a little time to warm up.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website. Here are some helpful tips:
•	All dogs listed on Petfinder are still available. 
•	Please DO NOT use the "Ask About Me" tab on this page. We DO NOT receive these inquiries.
•	We CANNOT move forward until we receive an application. Even if you're only interested, please fill out an application at mnpitbull.com. We will respond within 24-48 hours (M-F) after receiving your inquiry. 
• Adoption fees are as follows: 2-5 months old: $400, 6-9 months old: $350, 10+ months old: $250. This covers their Spay/Neuter, Vaccinations, Microchip, 4DX, Fecal Tests, and Housing Costs. ********************************************************************************************************
Hi, I'm Poppy!

I'm around 10 months old and originally from TX. I was found on the streets with a severe case of mange. MPBR rescued me and fixed me up and now I'm a beautiful white and tan lady with a grey brindle. I'm medium in size so I can fit perfectly into your life! I know how to sit, shake, and stay. I am potty trained and crate trained. I'm still working on laying down and walking on a leash, but I'll get there. I'm staying in a home with a senior cat that I am very interested in. I try to be gentle with her and I love to cuddle with her. There is also another dog that I do like to play with but I'm not sure how I feel about living with him. I really think I'd like to be the only dog in the home, then I can truly bloom! Oh, did I tell you how much I LOVE humans?! I want to play with them, and I cuddle really hard with them. I also like to go on adventures with them. I haven't met any children yet. I think I would probably be better with older kids. In my downtime, I really like to chew on hard toys so please keep them stocked! You should really meet me; I promise I will melt your heart! Please give me a chance.

Note: Poppy has had fights with the resident dog which is why she is looking for a single dog home. As a result of this, a human was bit while splitting the dogs up.

If you’re interested in meeting Poppy, please see our adoption process and online application by going to www.mnpitbull.com

animal.description:
Approx. DOB: 6/14/17 Approx Weight: 65 Lbs
Adoption Fee: $175 includes a 2 week trial to ensure everyone's happiness!
Experienced dog owners only please! Jersey has been through alot in his life..and deserves a calm, loving home!
Jerseys ideal home is Someone who wants a companion dog to go everywhere with them. He rides great in the car. He's patient and sweet. Needs some basic training. Would make a great support dog. He is not fond of being left alone for long periods of time due to his past, so someone who is home a lot is ideal.
Fenced yard please!
He is ok with laid back/submissive type dogs his own size that he has met since we have had him and loves adult humans A LOT!
I have been neutered, vaccinated, heartworm tested negative, wormed and microchipped. If you are interested in adopting me, please complete the adoption application located at www.furrykidsrefuge.org/adoptadog and a dedicated volunteer will get back to you as soon as possible.
Furry Kids' Refuge is in need of good quality dog and puppy food with meat as the first ingredient. You can drop off donations at our weekly adoption events at the Lee's Summit Petco (1860 NW Chipman Road, Lee's Summit, MO), Saturdays only from Noon to 4:00 p.m. Donations are tax deductible as allowed by law.
Would you like to foster a Furry Kid? Furry Kids' Refuge will supply the food & vet care while you supply the basic house rules & love.......win-win for all!! Just visit our website http://www.furrykidsrefuge.org/category/fostering/ for more information. Thanks for your support!

animal.description:
Samson is 13 years old and weighs 19lbs. He is a very good boy and has good potty manners, most of the time. He loves hanging out on the couch with his foster mom but he doesn't jump on furniture. Samson gets along great with other dogs. 

We think Samson has had a rough life. He has a little trouble walking but gets around fine. Samson needs a home without steps or a swimming pool. He also takes thyroid medicine, his levels will need to be monitored and he needs daily eye drops We would love for Samson to find his forever home where he can receive the TLC he deserves. 

Please apply at tzuzoorescue.com if you are interested in adopting from Tzu Zoo Rescue.  More information available by contacting tzradopt@gmail.com.

[NOTE: We are a rescue NOT a shelter, meaning WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY THAT OPENS TO THE PUBLIC. Typically, an application and home visit (both of which are required for adoption) MUST be completed, BEFORE a potential adopter will be introduced to one of our pets, in order to first determine that our basic adoption requirements are met, prior to introductions being made. We also utilize personal reference and vet checks (to ensure that any pets already in the potential adoptive home are current on vaccines, heart worm prevention and sterilized) in our adoption process, all of which is intended to ensure that the best match, between pet and people, is made. The adoption fee is based on on the dog's age.

animal.description:
Hi friends,

Shiloh here.  I am a 2 year old Boxer/Lab mix.  Mixed with what else, we don't know but hey I'm cute!

My puppy friends and I were just dumped at a cemetary.  Some big meanies did that to us.  My friends were scared, but I wasn't.  I was like " I aint afraid of no ghost!"  (I really was but don't tell ;) )  Have you ever spent the night in a cemetary??  Lots of scary things going on there when it's dark, let me tell ya....

So, one day this lady came by and saw us and started taking videos.  We were running around and playing, because you know it was daylight and all.  Ghosts and ghouls don't usually come out in the daylight and vampires, well you know what happens to them if they do!  HAHAHAHAHA  Anyway, back to my story. So the lady taking the video?  She posted it straight to the Lucies Project page and next thing I know, here they come to rescue us.  How cool is that?  I sure would like to give that nice lady a big ole slurp on the face.  :)

Now, one of my friends and I are left here waiting for the coolest family to come visit us and considering adopting one or both of us.  Could that be you??  I sure hope so!!

*** We strive to ensure our dogs are going to a safe, loving and caring home. Phone interviews are required for all adoptions****

animal.description:
How can you even resist that smile? Meet pretty-in-pink Percy!

This sweetheart is about five years old and a pittie mix. She is super athletic and has the best personality. Percy loves going on walks, cuddling, and exploring the outdoors with her people. She adores older kids and would prefer to be your one-and-only pet. (Once you meet Percy, you won't need any others!)

Would you like a loyal companion who will love you unconditionally, even on bad hair days? A girl who will celebrate life's highs with you and be by your side during the lows? If you can give Percy the forever home she's been dreaming of, just call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 and say you think Percy's your girl! Percy is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, and ready to start her new life -- with you!

*Percy is at The Sanctuary by The Pet Connection in Beloit, Kansas, but transport is available to the right home. She's eligible for a no-cost adoption with an encouraged donation.

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET? Fill out an Adoption Application now! Appointments can also be made to meet a pet by calling us at 913-671-PETS (913-671-7387).  

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
Prior to adoption, our animals are: 
**Tested for diseases 
**Vaccinated 
**Spayed/neutered 
**Microchipped 

NO COST adoptions with an encouraged donation are accepted. 

The Pet Connection also offers adopters a FREE veterinary examination and a medical care support plan for 60 days after adoption, as well as lifetime behavioral training, safe sanctuary for pets returned in emergency situations, extensive assistance with lost and found pets, and other expert pet services in a variety of areas, including pet selection, behavioral issues, general training, nutrition, and transition to adoptive homes.

Please visit our website at www.thepetconnection.org for more information about The Pet Connection and for a full listing of our available pets, 

Call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you can foster, adopt, or sponsor a special needs dog or cat! 

The Pet Connection is a membership organization operating a no-kill adoption center located at 417 N Rawhide Suite H, Olathe, KS 66061.

animal.description:
Hey, there! Cooper here. What can I say, I’m an awesome JRT!

I’m young (about 3 years), active, and love to be active. My human hated to give me up, but this silly thing called a “pandemic” meant long hours, days, and nights away from me, so I’m hoping for another great chapter in life. I would love to find a human or family who is has lots of time to keep me busy. I would even love to learn some of those things Terriers “do” for sport, like agility, racing, and the like.

Even though I’m energetic, I can also be calm and chill, too, from “letting” you rub my belly (how nice of me) to falling asleep in your lap.

I haven’t been around cats here, but I’m just fine with the other dogs at the ranch and haven’t had any problem fitting in.

I AM high energy and I need a secure fence to keep me safe when I have the zoomies.  Not interested in chasing down balls but love to race with people or dogs (I win!)

So, whadda ya say? Are you ready to play?

Come see me at 

http://www.jackrusselladoptions.org/

Zeus is a beautiful GSD who is a warrior in this life- he’s overcome that much! Zeus came to us originally with the rest of his family (whom have all been adopted) after his previous owners couldn’t care for him. Zeus’ life prior to coming to the rescue was a hard one of living outside and fighting for scraps; hence the scars on his face. 

Zeus as a result of his past, has come a long way in his socialization with humans in his time with us, but is still considered by the average public to be “skittish.” He loves having a safe space, his crate, to go to when the world is too much. Zeus will need a family that can see past the scars on his face to the loving, tender heart beneath, and is patient and kind with him. Zeus loves to play with other dogs when he thinks no one is watching; seeing him kick up his heels is the sort of wholesome delight we all need.

Zeus would benefit from multiple meet and greets with his potential family, to ensure maximum comfort for both family and Zeus. For this reason we are only accepting local applications.

----
Peach County Animal Rescue is a rescue located in Fort Valley, GA. Our adoption fees range from $250-350+. Although our rescue dogs share a common bond with one another, no rescue story is the same (even when similar). Vetting costs vary depending on their health conditions. All of our dogs are fully vetted: up-to-date on annual shots, spayed/neutered and microchipped with a lifetime registration. We look forward to hearing from you!

If you would like to send in an application for this dog, please use the link below! https://peachcountyanimalrescueandrehabilitation.org/apply-now-2/

animal.description:
Beautiful Shelby has a couple of requirements for her forever family: 1. Must love pizza! It’s Shelby’s absolute favorite food and she refuses to be adopted by any pizza haters . 2. This may be number two but it’s equally in important- Shelby must be allowed to have her space. Shelby is a gentle, low maintenance girl who enjoys her alone time in her crate. A crate is a must for this girl. It provides a retreat where she can go and feel safe when she is frightened. Shelby is frightened of many things including fireworks, thunderstorms and meeting new people. Shelby has never shown aggression towards meeting strangers, she just prefers to hide in her crate where she knows she is safe. Shelby would love a confident and gentle, male companion to play with and show her that life isn’t all that scary. She currently enjoys playing with her male foster sibling and we think another male dog in her new home will help her adjust. Shelby loves when her humans make silly noises and having a consistent routine makes her very happy! Shelby takes longer to warm up to women than men, but in time she will learn to trust. We understand that a dog who likes their space and prefers not to be touched is not for everyone, but we know the pyrfect family is out there for Miss Shelby. Shelby would love her new humans to live a quiet life, with not many visitors or guests. Shelby will do things on her own time. It will be very rewarding to watch Shelby slowly come out of her shell. She may never conquer some of her fears, so her new humans need to be ok with that. If there’s one thing that we do know will help, it’s PIZZA! So what do you say? Does this sweet, gentle and low maintenance girl sound like she would fit in with your low key, pizza-loving lifestyle? Apply today to give Shelby a chance at a peaceful furever!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

Hank is very strong and muscular, but he is very friendly. He was a stray, so he has been fending for himself for a while. The homeowners in the area were getting upset with him for getting into their trash. He was hungry and only trying to find food to eat. He is between 2 and 3 years old and weighs 85 pounds. He's quite a good-looking fella and would love a home with some space to run and sniff around. He mostly wants to just be outside and do his houndy sniffing. He has learned to walk well on the leash since he is one of the "regulars" walked by our volunteers. Take a good look at this nice boy and see if he is a good fit for you. He deserves a second chance! Can you give him one?

Message from our dog walkers:

I am pretty sure Santa Paws made an appearance in Jackson County. This big lap dog is such a great dog and well behaved even as we dressed him. I love this boy and you will too. He likes to walk and enjoys spending time with his peeps! He really would love to find a home and forever family before Christmas!

When Hank arrived at the shelter he was so afraid he really didn't want to walk... He is so improved! He loves to be leashed up and go for walks now and he is not happy if you leash another dog before he gets to go! He is a great dog but like Miss Amelia, he is not a fan of posing for pictures so this picture doesn't do him justice, he is a very handsome dog!!! Hank could be dog selective

1/27/2021 Hank has made such progress since his arrival. Originally, he was afraid of his own shadow. Now Hank is friendly, loving, excited to go on walks, and has decent manners on a leash. He is definitely a volunteer favorite and so ready for his forever home!

animal.description:
****PETronus Rescue endeavors to include all pertinent information for each of the dogs within our organization with regard to approximate age, potty training status, kennel training status, temperament, activity level, dog/cat friendliness, etc in an effort to give those considering adopting as much information as we have.  Inquiries requesting additional information will not be returned, due to limited volunteers. Thank you for your understanding **** 

Meet Heath.

Heath was picked up off the streets by a Good Samaritan. He was wondering with a female, Arya, and was the daddy of her surprise litter of puppies.

Heath is a playful guy, who does well with female dogs. No male dogs and no cats for this guy. He loves to play in the yard, has good leash manners and his foster has been working with him on some obedience training as well! He can be in a home with older children who will respect his boundaries and not poke and prod at him. 

All PETronus Rescue dogs receive basic vaccinations (distemper/parvo, bordetella, & rabies), spay/ neuter, and microchip prior to adoption. We also treat any know medical issues, including heartworms.

Our dogs live in foster homes while they wait patiently for their forever families to find them. This is beneficial in that they learn house manners, crate training, housebreaking, etc while they wait and we are also able to get a very realistic picture of their energy level, temperament, etc so that we can place them in a home that is the best fit.

Our adoption fees are $200 for dogs over 1 year of age and $250 for dogs under 1 year of age. Puppies receive 3 rounds of puppy vaccinations.

If you are interested in adopting one of our amazing dogs, please fill out our adoption application here http://bit.ly/PRAdoption and we will be in touch!

Ideal home with be with very active people that can take him for runs as he gets bored very quickly. A ranch style home will be great however, he can be in a smaller place as far as he gets plenty of DAILY exercise. 

He is crate trained; and loves his crate in case you need to go out for several hours; that will be the safest place for him - he loves a good bone to chew on.
He is special needs because he needs special hepatic food - he has been tested and he is in good health now.

He will give you lots of years of unconditional love; will hug you, will give you a high five, and will cuddle with you - he is very verbal.

He loves to play ball and fetch as well - so a young kid will be a great partner for him. He loves his human family and will never be aggressive towards people - 

He went through abandonment; and he is very loyal and protective as well. It takes a special person to get this special 4 leg guy:)

Of course, he has been neutered and has received his yearly DHLPP vaccines, dewormed; deflead; a free health check up by our participating pet clinic.

We are scheduling meet & greet adoption appointments and keeping a distance protocol. No appointments will be made unless we have received an application; therefore, we can match you with the best fit for you.

Please text at 619-576-0747 or email veronica.aaofusa@gmail.com or visit our website at www.aaofus.org and complete our application at the following link:
http://aaofus.org/adoption-application.html

Due to high volume of calls; NO PHONE calls are accepted at this time - therefore, please text us or email us.

LIVE!! LOVE!!! RESCUE!! ADOPT A HOMELESS PET AND SAVE A LIFE!!!

Follow us on Instagram @aaofus

3 years old.

1.	I am a Mastiff-Dane mix, and I am about 4 years old.

animal.description:
Baby Girl is a 2 year old spayed female Cattle Dog mix. 

**Baby Girl is shown by appointment only. For more information or to schedule an appointment, contact Rachael at rwilson@midlandshumanesociety.org or (712)396-2265**

Baby Girl is a very shy girl, looking for a laid back home. Baby Girl needs a very patient owner who can let her acclimate at her own shell. 

Baby Girl is very skittish, especially with new situations, loud noises & fast movements. She will need more time than most other dogs to decompress. She will most likely need to spend the first few weeks on leash, inside & outside, so she learns to look to her people for guidance & helps eliminate her possibly escaping.

animal.description:
Hey guys I’m Colby! 
My foster mom told me I needed to tell you all about myself because my forever mommy/daddy needs to find me! I hear a lot of about this “forever home” and “forever family” and it sounds amazing! I'm a little over a year old.  I hope my forever family has a comfy couch with a spot for me. My favorite past time is snuggling on the couch with my humans. Snuggles are the best! I also really hope they have lots of tennis balls. Tennis balls are my favorite and even though I’m not the best at catching them, the chase is the fun anyway!
Before my foster mom and dad took me in, I stayed with my best bud for a few weeks. My best bud is my trainer. He taught me all of these fun human words that I understand now! I make people really happy when they see I know human words! It’s super easy to learn the human words and he will even teach you them! If I got to pick my forever home I really hope it’s just grown adults and possibly a dog brother or sister. I love to play so a canine sibling sounds great! 
I am really hoping to find my humans soon! Are you my mommy or daddy? Kobe will have a few training sessions with his new family and his trainer. For this reason his new family needs to live in the Charlotte area.

animal.description:
Indy is a 4 year old pyr girl who is in search of a new home through no fault of her own. She came to us in August of 2020 from Edgar County Animal Shelter in Paris, IL where she was surrendered by her owner because he sold his goats and no longer needed her  When she came into rescue she was unspayed and heartworm and Lyme disease positive.  She has since been treated for heartworm and  Lyme disease, and spayed.  Both of these diseases are easily preventable with monthly flea, tick and heartworm preventatives.  Indy was adopted in the fall of 2020, but her adopters were unfamiliar with the breed, and she proved to not be a good fit for them. Indy is very sweet and gentle girl.  She gets along with other dogs, is fine with cats, and is very calm with children. She is a little skittish at first with strangers but warms up once she knows you. Indy does well getting a bath and being brushed.  She rides well in vehicles. Indy can be left on her own without being crated.  Indy does like to bark, so if barking is a concern for you, you may want to consider another breed.  She also needs work on coming inside; since she was a livestock guardian originally, crossing door thresholds, can be a challenge at first. We recommend that you attend obedience training to help you create a special bond with you and your new friend, and so you have a well behaved canine. Great Pyrenees are willing to learn, but are not as eager to comply with commands as much as other breeds. They are bred to be independent thinkers. Applicants must be over 25, own their own home and all children in household must be over 6 years old. Your resident pets must be up to date on vaccines, sterilized, you must have a good history of vet care for them, and you must have used heartworm preventative year round for your dogs. 


Indy will be placed as an inside pet with outside privileges. You MUST have a securely fenced yard accessible from your home. Invisible fencing does not work with this breed and they will take the shock for the freedom.  Great Pyrenees are bred to roam and will create their own territory if not secured, which can led to them being lost, hit by vehicles or shot by people who see them as a threat. The breed is not a good off leash dog, and cannot be trusted to not run away.  A Great Pyrenees off leash is a " DisAPyr." 

If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please complete the appropriate application on our website, www.igpr.org under the Adopt tab. 

All of our dogs marked as needing foster homes are also available for adoption.  If a dog is listed on this site, it is available.  No need to contact us to see if it is,  We do require you  complete the adoption application prior to meeting a dog.

We also offer a foster to adopt program. You foster the dog, and have first right of refusal on them if an approved application is submitted for them. 

In fostering a dog, the dog comes to you fully vetted. and groomed. You provide good quality food, grooming, and we provide the heartworm preventative and medical care, if needed* .(*Based on approval from IGPR.)

Adoption fee is $350

Due to his mobility issues (he takes very small steps - shuffles like an old man – and has arthritis in his front elbows, fractured pelvis and hip dysplasia in both back legs), the best home is with no stairs. animal.description:
Eva is an old soul who prefers the simple things in life: watching over the yard, car rides, swimming, and a dollop of peanut butter after a long day of lounging. She is housebroken, leash trained, has excellent house manners and knows basic commands. After a successful career as a livestock guardian, Eva is looking to live out her best years in a peaceful retirement home. Her animal guarding days came to an end when she tore her ACL protecting a flock from coyotes. Now it’s time for Eva to relax and enjoy her golden years. Eva’s pyrfect oasis consists of a quiet home, with a big yard all to herself, where she can quietly keep watch. Eva is on meds for thyroid and arthritis and she would like you to know that she would take her pills on her own if she had thumbs, but she does not, so she’ll need a family who can help her with these things :) Eva would do best as an only dog, as she gets defensive of other dogs in her space. She’s never been around small children, so older is better for this big gal. She is great meeting most people though slow to warm up to some. She’s not a fan of manicures, humans messing with her food and thunder. She is a fan of the vet, a good brushing and her groomer at PetSmart :) Eva is a very gentle, sweet soul with so much love still to give. She’s a well-mannered, easy going gal who will make the right family very happy. So what do you say? Will you help Eva get to her well-deserved retirement? Apply for this lovely girl today!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.
